title: pepper slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, shredding cabbage and chopping pepper and onion; set aside.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and mustard seed in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir to mix and pour over cabbage; mix well and chill.

title: cole slaw dressing(original recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Better if allowed to set overnight (refrigerated).

title: apple salad
directions: Chop or cut all fruit to desired size.
Chop walnuts.
Chop or cut candy or omit.
Combine all ingredients and chill.
tags: Dream Whip or heavy whipping cream

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Alternate layers in crock-pot:
hamburger, sausage, noodles, soup, sauce, onion, pepperoni and cheese.
Heat 4 hours on low.

title: bisquick chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken in 1-quart salted water until tender.
Cook chopped onion with chicken.
Cool, pour broth off and debone. Place deboned chicken in baking dish.
Add cream of cream soup and 1 cup chicken broth.
Combine remaining ingredients for batter. Pour batter over and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Pour 1/2 cup broth over pie when taken from oven. Extra broth may be used as a gravy or sauce.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly combine all ingredients except hash browns.
Place hash browns in a greased 2 qt. baking dish.
Add mixture to hash browns and stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set 8 hours, then roll in nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Set 1/4 cup of stuffing
aside.
Mix
all other ingredients and put in casserole
dish.
Sprinkle
of stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: baked sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Arrange cooked Brussels sprouts in shallow (1 1/2-quart) baking dish.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; blend. Pour over Brussels sprouts and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes until tender or lightly brown.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: green chile cheese cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray square pan with nonfat cooking spray (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Measure all ingredients in order listed in bowl; stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake in an 8-inch pan 45 minutes or a 9-inch pan 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: ole' barbecue bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Stir in chilies and sauce. Spoon into baking dish.

title: baked ziti
directions: Boil ziti and drain.
Mix Ricotta cheese with eggs and parsley.
Layer 1 large aluminum pan with sauce, then add a layer of ziti.
Next add layer of Ricotta cheese mixture then a layer of Mozzarella (sliced thin).
Add sauce and repeat layers.
Sprinkle each layer with Locatelli cheese to taste.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Test center.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend at high speed for 1 minute, stopping once to stir down.
Bake on ungreased griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Makes 20 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: pita pizza
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon tomato sauce over each pita round. Sprinkle with oregano.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Set pizza under broiler about 4 inches from heat and broil until cheese bubbles (3 minutes).

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, beating often.
Add butter, syrup and vanilla.
Arrange pecans in pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: danish wedding cookies
directions: With mixer, cream together butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Beat in nuts. Shape into balls approximately 1/2 inch diameter.
Gently flatten partially with the back of a spoon.
(I keep back of spoon lightly coated with flour.)
Do not flatten too much.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 375 degrees.
Do not brown.
When moderately cool, roll in sifted powdered sugar.

title: florentine dip with artichokes
directions: May use low-fat version of ingredients.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Put 18 marshmallows in pan with crushed pineapple.
Cook on low heat until marshmallows melt.
Set aside and cool.
Put milk in small bowl and whip until it forms stiff peaks.
Fold pineapple mixture into whipped milk.
Mix well.
Put in baked 9-inch pie shell and refrigerate for 24 hours before cutting.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine cooked macaroni, onion, celery, carrots and egg whites only.
Then mash egg yolks.
Add sugar, Miracle Whip, vinegar, salt, mustard and evaporated milk; mix well.
Add to macaroni mixture and chill overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: german cheese ball
directions: Cream cheeses together first, then add other ingredients.
Mix just long enough to blend together.
Garnish with what you like.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together; keep in jar.
For one cup of tea, use two heaping teaspoonfuls of mix.
For 6-cup teapot, use 1/2 cup of mix.

title: sauerkraut and sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 1 inch pieces.
Rinse sauerkraut; add sugar and sausage.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Blend soup and water and sour cream. In
quart
casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, soup mix, salt, pepper and onion.
Top with chops.
Cover and bake at 375° for
1 1/4 hours.
This can be put in microwave, leaving out
the chops
until the final 4 minutes of cooking. Cook on Medium-high for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add grits; cook until thick, then add a little of the hot mixture to egg and milk.
Then add cheese, margarine, salt and garlic powder; mix until smooth.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Will serve 6.

title: spinach salad
directions: Drain spinach.
Squeeze out excess water and mix all ingredients together.
Chill for a couple of hours or overnight.

title: triple cheese bread(for your bread machine)
directions: Put ingredients into your bread machine and bake as directed.

title: angel food pie
directions: Put first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
When cool, refrigerate until set.
Fold in pineapple, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put mixture into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Decorate with cherries.

title: crumb cake
directions: Using pastry blender, mix flour, sugar, spices and shortening until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to crumb mixture and stir until well blended.
Put batter in 9 x 13 pan and top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cover with lid.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to the boiling point.
Sift flour and salt into liquid.
Stir until a ball is formed which slips from the side of the pan.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each egg is added.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creme pie filling
directions: Mix in double boiler, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk; cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly until thick.
Add egg yolks and cook 3 more minutes. Add butter; cool and add vanilla.
Add chocolate or coconut if desired.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer as listed in microwave-safe deep casserole dish (spread softened cream cheese).
Cover and microwave until cheese melts.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix rice, sugar, pineapple and vanilla.
Stir in marshmallows and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients into a batter.
Peel and slice onion and separate into rings.
Dip rings into batter and drop in hot oil right away.
It's best to make batter ahead and let set a bit. Take fork to handle onion rings and drain on paper toweling; sprinkle with a little salt or seasoned salt.
Eat soon after.

title: cranberry pecan muffins
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Fold in sour cream. Combine flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Fill 2 1/2-inch diameter paper-lined muffin cups half full.
Top each muffin with a mixture of the final two ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to bubbly stage, stirring. Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press rest into baking pan.
Spread raisins and sauce over the top.
Then sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: two by four soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese and add Rotel. Add meat to mixture and a can of water.
Let ingredients simmer. When soup is warm throughout, add cans of minestrone soup.	Reheat soup.
Pour over fritos.
Serves 8.
(Cut in half for fewer people.)

title: viennese mocha coffee mix
directions: Place dry milk, sugar, coffee powder, cocoa powder and cinnamon in a blender container.
Cover and blend until very fine. Store in an airtight container in a cool place.

title: pizza party snacks
directions: Fry pork sausage until brown.
Drain well.
Melt cheese and add other ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Bake at 400 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; saute onions, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Melt garlic cheese on soup.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole and bake at 350° until hot through (about 30 minutes). Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: oyster-artichoke soup
directions: In heavy 4-quart pot, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add artichokes and sprinkle with flour.
Stir to coat, but do not brown.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add oysters, with liquid, and sherry.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Do not boil.
Stir in half and half and milk.
Cool and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Before serving, heat slowly over low heat.
Serves 8 bowls or 16 cups.

title: almond braid
directions: Mix 1 1/2 c of the flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast in large bowl.
Cut margarine into small pieces; combine with milk and water.
Heat until warm (105-115 degrees).
Stir into dry ingredients. Stir in eggs, almonds, peel, nutmeg and enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Grease top of dough and cover tightly; refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: hungarian noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute garlic in butter and add onion.
Combine all ingredients. Bake in a greased 10 x 6 baking dish for 25 minutes.

title: e-z cherry cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Drizzle the melted butter over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with "plain" whipped cream or ice cream.

title: supper slaw
directions: Chop cauliflower.
Chop broccoli or break apart.
Chop onions and celery; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix cole slaw mix as instructed.
Toss.
Chill.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and pecans.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press evenly and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cracklin cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into well oiled, greased hot pan. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant 1/4-inch thick.
Dip slices into bowl with beaten eggs then coat eggplant with mixture of bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Fry in hot olive oil.
When lightly browned remove from oil and drain on paper towels.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion and celery; drain.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms, rice, soup and water.
Put in a 3-quart casserole. Bake for 1 hour, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered, at 350°. Serves 6 to 10.

title: wild rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Blend together cake mix, 2 eggs and butter; beat accordingly to directions of cake mix.
Pour into oblong pan. Batter is very stiff.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
You can substitute onion powder instead of onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix everything, except soda, in a large skillet.
Cook until peanuts start popping, 6 to 12 minutes, and color starts to turn light brown.
Set aside and add soda.
Stir thoroughly and quickly.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: best beef stew
directions: Chop the onion; toss the beef with the flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Heat the oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add the meat, in batches if necessary, and brown it on all sides. Remove.
Add the onion; cover and cook over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes.
Return the meat to the pot with the stock and the marjoram.
Cover and simmer until the meat is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Meanwhile, halve the carrots lengthwise and then cut them crosswise into 1-inch chunks.
Add the carrots and the potatoes to the pot with 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Cook until the vegetables are tender, 45 to 50 minutes.
Taste for seasoning and add more salt and pepper as needed.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Add all ingredients. Toss together.
Spread on shallow cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes, until light brown. Reduce heat to 225° and bake until dry; stir occasionally.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for meat.
Combine mixture and meat in a bowl.
Cover and soak overnight.
Run toothpicks through meat and hang on rack in oven.
Bake at 150° for about 8 hours.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Open cans of beans; drain. Chop pepper. Combine all beans and pepper together. Place oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a jar; shake well. Pour over beans. Chill overnight.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with water, bring to boil, simmer 1 minute, turn off heat, cover and soak for 1 hour. Drain and discard water.

title: spanish cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon pieces until done, but not crisp.
Saute onion, bell pepper and potatoes in bacon grease. Push to the sides and add cabbage to fry.
Turn over a few times to catch some of that fattening bacon grease.
Season with fajita seasoning powder or just salt and pepper will do.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, juice included.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Additional water may be needed to cook cabbage, but when cabbage softens, cook water out.
Serves 4 to 6.
Use as a side dish with Mexican food.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter; mix with graham crackers.
Bake just a few minutes.
Put bananas in crust, then pour cream cheese mixture over bananas, then another layer of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat water in a large pan; when boiling, add crumbled meat. Cover and cook 2 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until meat is cooked.
Turn to low; skim off meat residue until clear.
Do not drain.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the Ritz crackers and butter. Pour in a casserole dish.
Melt butter and crackers.
Spread crackers over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Combine all other ingredients with meat/onion mixture and pour in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fox and hounds pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes. Blend in melted chocolate.
Spread 1 cup of mixture over baked pie crust.
Set aside rest.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped peanuts over chocolate mixture.

title: fig cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil until well blended.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well after each one.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, soda, salt and allspice.
Add flour mixture alternating with buttermilk and add fig preserves.
Stir in pecans. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hot turkey sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly with hands to evenly distribute spices.
Shape into patties and refrigerate (covered) up to several hours.

title: aunt lil's gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add egg and then molasses and mix well.
Add hot water with baking soda mixed in it.
Next, add flour, spices and salt and mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so.
Serve warm with hard sauce, lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread onto crescent dough.
Add mixture of vegetables and press into cream cheese mixture.
Top with cheese and press.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon rub pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until brown and top is set.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Cook all ingredients, except brown sugar, in 3/4 cup water until carrots are fork-tender.
Add brown sugar; cook until dissolved.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add oil and milk.
Blend well and roll out between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Makes enough for a 2 crust pie.

title: potluck
directions: Fry pork loin cubes with onions.
Add water.
Cube potatoes; slice carrots.
Add to mixture; season to taste.
When vegetables are cooked, thicken mixture of water, cornstarch and Gravy Master.

title: mom's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Very chunky.
Yum!

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ground chuck, egg, bread crumbs, milk, salt and nutmeg; mix.
Shape into 60 (3/4-inch) balls.

title: virginia's homemade ice cream(rich peoples' dessert)
directions: Blend ingredients except for berries.
Add enough additional milk to bring to almost full line of freezer.
After almost frozen, add enough berries to taste, about 2 cartons.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce, tomato paste and garlic powder.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart greased baking dish.

title: kototz(polish bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Cool milk and add sugar.
Stir.
Add yeast and work in the other ingredients. Let dough rise.
Place in 2 loaf pans (9 x 5-inches) or you can use 2 cake pans (9-inch round).

title: chocolate pudding in a cloud
directions: Mix pudding according to
directions
on box.
Put Cool Whip in dessert cups, leave a
hole
in the center of each cup for the pudding.
Place pudding
in
the
center of Cool Whip. Pudding will be circled by Cool Whip.
Any instant pudding mix may be used.

title: cream cheese chewies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together and put in pan.
Put chopped nuts over cake mix layer.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together and put over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until particles are fine (like pie dough).
Add milk, egg and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Dough may be refrigerated, if desired.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch.
Cut out in shapes; decorate with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8
minutes.

title: chicken breasts and broccoli
directions: Bake chicken breasts, then debone and remove skin.
Put, in casserole dish, one breast, then broccoli (if frozen, put into casserole frozen) along side and so on, until all are used.
Add creamed soup.

title: red and green apple salad
directions: In large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
Cover and refrigerate.
Prior to serving, combine sour cream and mayo and pour over apples and toss.
Stir in dates, nuts and cherries.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob into bowl, making sure to scrape milky white substance from cob.
(You should have about 4 cups of kernels.) Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add corn, cream (if using), salt and pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally for 10 to 15 minutes or until corn is tender.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in Crisco in a large skillet. Add beef and brown well.
Add tomato juice, rice, chili powder and seasonings.
Pour into casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: parmesan dinner rolls
directions: Slice each thawed loaf into 10 pieces; roll into balls.
Roll each dough ball first in margarine then in grated cheese.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: the other baked potato
directions: Combine in 2-quart dish.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are tender.

title: spinach salad
directions: The night before serving, mix first 8 ingredients together in a pint jar and shake well.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Blend with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of mixture in ungreased pan.
Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling over crumbs.
Cover with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Blend
coconut,
pecans,
condensed milk, margarine and sugar together.
Shape into small balls.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Melt
paraffin
and chocolate bits in small saucepan over low heat (10 to 15 minutes).
Insert toothpick into balls and dip into chocolate paraffin mixture.

title: potato chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove, drain and crumble.
Saute onion and carrots in fat.
Drain all but enough fat to make a smooth mixture with 2 tablespoons flour.
Add flour, stir and cook for a few minutes until browned.
Add potatoes, water and seasonings.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add milk.
Reheat until hot.
Mash with potato masher if desired. Sprinkle bacon bits on top and garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water, chocolate and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth; cool.
In bowl sift together flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder and salt; make a well in center.
Add cooking oil, egg yolks, 3/4 cup water and vanilla.
Beat egg yolk mixture at high speed of electric mixer for 5 minutes or until satin smooth.
Stir in chocolate mixture.

title: no bake thumbprints
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup frosting.
In a large bowl combine frosting, graham crackers and margarine.
Blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and immediately roll in ground nuts.
With finger, make imprint in center.
Place in single layer pan.
In small bowl, blend reserved frosting and cream cheese until smooth.
Spoon mixture into center of cookie.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Divide between 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: festive corn dip
directions: *Or 1 can white whole kernel corn and 1 can yellow corn and a 2-ounce jar diced pimentos.

title: stir-fry pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on plastic wrap.
Pound slighlty.
Sprinkle seasoned salt and salt-free lemon pepper seasoning.
Do not cut pork chops up.
Heat large skillet or wok with oil on medium heat. Put pork chops in skillet for 3 minutes until lightly browned. Toss onions and green peppers.
Add soy sauce and stir until slightly browned.
Serve with your choice of vegetables. Preparation time: 20 minutes.
Cooking time:
25 to 35 minutes.

title: grog
directions: Combine in saucepan; heat until red hots dissolve.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield:
24 half-cup servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients together; stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Ice, if desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat together sugar, flour and eggs.
Add butter, buttermilk, salt and vanilla.
Beat all together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm and golden brown (about 35 minutes).

title: easy oven pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in oven.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt, flour and milk and blend well.
Pour mixture over melted oleo in baking pan and sprinkle cinnamon all over.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot with maple syrup.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup oleo in a 3-quart baking dish.
Mix potatoes, onions, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix cornflakes with remaining oleo; put on top of mixture in casserole.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are done.

title: skroodle salad
directions: Mix beans, vegetables, noodles, pimentos, pepper, onion, celery and celery seed together and set aside.
Mix salt, oleo, sugar, vinegar, cornstarch and mustard together and cook until thickened.
Pour over first mixture and let stand overnight.

title: stuffed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool and remove meat from bones. Arrange chicken meat in a shallow 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl, combine soup, pimento, 2/3 cup evaporated milk, spread mixture over chicken.
Toss together stuffing mix and remaining milk until all milk is absorbed.
Spread over mixture in casserole then sprinkle cheese and parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: apple tea
directions: Boil for 5 minutes or until hearts melt.
Let set for 30 minutes.

title: apricot-cranberry tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Roll each dough portion into a 12 inch circle on a lightly floured surface.
Cut dough into 36 circles with 2 1/2 inch round cutter.
Press 1 dough circle into each of 36 miniature muffin cups.
Press into the bottoms and up the sides of muffin cups.
Bake at 425 degrees for 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and cool on wire racks.

title: lemon snowball
directions: Line a 12 cup bowl with 2 pieces of waxed paper, one on top of other crosswise.
Set bowl aside.
In a large bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add boiling water, stir until dissolved.
Stir in granulated sugar, salt, orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and peel.
Refrigerate 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until partially set and mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.

title: grammy's overnight pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti according to package directions.
Add 1/2 salad dressing and toss until spaghetti is well oiled.
Add cucumbers, peppers, tomato, celery and onion.
Add the rest of dressing.
Toss well.
Refrigerate overnight, tossing several times.

title: cherry nut pie
directions: Add lemon juice to the condensed milk and stir real well. Drain all juice out of the cherries and add to mixture.
Add pecans and Cool Whip and stir well.
Put mixture in 2 graham cracker crusts and chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.
This also freezes well.

title: carrot cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots and vanilla; beat until blended.
Stir in coconut, 1/2 cup nuts and pineapple.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is baking, prepare icing.

title: traditional english muffins in a loaf(2 loaves)
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°). Add to dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in remaining 3 cups of flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from draft, for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: peanut butter candy squares
directions: Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, salt and soda in a large bowl.
Melt margarine.
Stir in vanilla and Karo.
Pour over oat mixture; mix well.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spoon crunchy peanut butter over hot candy.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread mixture over candy, making swirls and cool. Makes 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix in large pan.
Marinate 2 or 3 hours.
Place on cookie sheets and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Turn them over after 20 minutes.

title: family pie
directions: Mix 1 handful of forgiveness, 1 full pound of unselfishness and 1 heaping cupful of love together smoothly with complete faith in God.
Add 2 tablespoons wisdom and 1 teaspoon good nature for flavor.
Finally, sprinkle generously with thoughtfulness.

title: brownie mix
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: smoked fish from a key wester
directions: Marinate fish in brine for 24 hours.
Wipe dry and let stand for one hour.
Smoke in your smoker for 4 to 5 hours.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all in blender. Mix 3 minutes. Pour into greased deep-dish pie pan (9-inch). Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: yummy vanilla banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Layer wafers, bananas, and mixture.
(Makes several layers).

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
In a saucepan, heat milk over medium heat until bubbles appear around edges of pan.
Stir cornmeal slowly into milk.
Cook 10 minutes, or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add sugar, molasses, salt, cinnamon, ginger and baking soda; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 2 hours or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken) and layer in casserole with chicken, beginning and ending with stuffing mix.
Top with chopped pimento.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sante fe chicken
directions: Season chicken as desired.
Grill chicken.
During last few minutes of grilling time, sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Let cheese melt.
Remove from grill.
Cover chicken with chopped onions and tomatoes.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Heat oil in 6-quart saucepan.
Add onions and cook for 2 minutes.
Add ground chuck and garlic (or garlic powder) and cook until meat browns.
Place whole tomatoes in blender and then add to meat mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat to low and simmer, covered, for about four hours. Remove bay leaves.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Mix together and set aside the soups and salsa.
Then layer chips, chicken, sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up.
Bake uncovered at 350° until hot.
Can be made the day before and put in refrigerator and then baked before serving.

title: torsh
directions: Simmer fish for 20 minutes in the sugar, salt and water mixture.
Put butter on both sides and broil for 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Serve with melted butter.

title: fluffy seafoam frosting
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, beating with electric mixer.
Beat until mixture stands in stiff, straight peaks.
Remove from heat. Add the vanilla.
Continue beating until thick enough to spread.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; blend in eggs and beat well at low speed.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin.
Stir in chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 6-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add eggs, applesauce, sweetener and cooking oil.
Mix well.
Blend into baking soda and flour.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs from cheesecake mix and margarine.
Press cheesecake mixture in bottom of a rectangular pan.
Spread softened ice cream over crust.
Freeze.
Combine cheesecake filling and milk.
Blend at low speed until blended; add pumpkin.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Spread cheesecake mixture over ice cream layer.
Apply seal and freeze several hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake at 375° until nicely browned.

title: yellow summer squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine squash and onion in large saucepan.
Cover with water.
Season with salt, if desired.
Cook 5 minutes; drain.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Scrape and wash potatoes.
Mix parsley with butter or margarine.
Roll potatoes in the parsley and oil mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Blend chipped beef in the blender or food processor until the beef is a crumbly mixture.
Mix with the mixer the cream cheese, milk, mayonnaise, mustard and 3 tablespoons of the chipped beef. Refrigerate the cream cheese mixture overnight.
Form in a ball and roll in the remaining chipped beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 2/3 cup boiling water.
Mix well with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugars in large bowl. Mix well. Add eggs; beat 1 minute, until well blended. Add vanilla; beat well. In separate bowl, combine flour, soda and cream of tartar. Add to creamed mixture. Drop by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: party spinach dip
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add cottage cheese; process until smooth, scraping sides of processor bowl once.
Place in a medium bowl; set aside.
Squeeze spinach until barely moist.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients to cheese mixture; stir well.
Cover; refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: caroli's chicken
directions: Boil water and cook noodles.
Do not add seasoning packages. At the same time, saute cut up chicken pieces.
Saute veggies until tender.
Add chicken and noodles to veggie mixture. Sprinkle seasoning packages over mixture; toss together.
Add soy sauce and water to season further.

title: miniature beef turnovers(appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground meat, drain excess fat. Combine first 5 ingredients, then brown a little longer until all ingredients are mixed.
Separate crescent dough as package directs, then cut each piece in half.
Place spoonful of mixture in center of each triangle.
Fold over and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 5 minutes or until golden.
Makes 48 turnovers.

title: apple pie
directions: Sprinkle apple slices with lemon juice; mix.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt.
Mix with apples.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with apple mixture.
Adjust top crust; brush with milk.
Sprinkle sugar until lightly covered, then cinnamon.
Slit top crust for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Nuts and raisins are optional.

title: tater tot salmon bake
directions: In 3-quart bowl, mix all except the potatoes.
Steam veggies 8 to 10 minutes before adding to mix.
Turn into 12 x 8 or 9 x 10-inch baking dish.
Arrange Tater Tots on top of dish.
Bake near center of oven and bake at 350°, until bubbly.
Remove from oven and allow to stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8. May be reheated in microwave.
If you prefer, skin and bone salmon before mixing.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon together for 10 minutes and combine with fruits.
Put into jars.
Best if let stand several days before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
In
saucepan combine next 4 ingredients until butter melts.
Stir
in
yeast
mixture.
Add 1 cup flour; beat until dough
is
elastic.
Add
eggs,
gradually	stir in 2 1/2 cups flour
to form a stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead dough for 15 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, cover, let rise, until doubled.
Divide
dough
in
half. Cut each 1/2 into 8 pieces. Shape
each
piece into a ball, dip into melted butter.
Place in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, sprinkle with herbs.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: low-fat baked apples
directions: Arrange an apple in a glass casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon in center of apple.
Pour Diet Rite over apples so pan is about half full.
Cover dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 1. Contains 60 calories, 0 g protein, 0 g fat, 0 mg chol. and 3 mg sodium.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: squash salad
directions: In food processor, chop one at a time all vegetables, except cucumbers.
Cut cucumbers up with knife.
Process lemon.
Mix well and serve.

title: creamy frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into rectangular pan.
Freeze overnight.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, egg and chopped apples with beater.
Combine flour and soda; add to egg mixture. Fold in nuts and raisins (optional). Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan; bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: roll out butter cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Let dough chill for 1 hour. Roll out to 1/8-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix and cook 1st 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Take from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Break graham crackers in half and place in large baking pan.
Pour mixture over graham crackers. Bake 10 minutes at 300°.
May line pan in foil for convenience.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, drain and chop broccoli.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over broccoli in casserole dish. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° until bubbly and firm on top.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing. Spread over rolls. Decorate with veggies, then add cheese.
Will keep 1 week in refrigerator.

title: sweet milk corn bread
directions: Boil water with butter in it, then add to meal. Add to other ingredients. Cook at 375°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 65 minutes at 350°.
Remove cake from pan after 10 minutes.
Cool and top with cream cheese frosting.

title: mud
directions: Combine pudding and chocolate chips in a "container." Make "crumbs" with chocolate cookies by putting them in a blender for a few seconds.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of pudding mixture.
Tuck gummi worms in pudding.
(Great for parties.
Container could be almost anything, including a new sand bucket.)

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix well and eat!

title: spanish american rice
directions: Heat
oil in skillet; cook onions slowly for 5 minutes. Add pepper,
celery and garlic; cook another minute.
Stir in sausage chunks
and saute, stirring now and then for another 5 minutes. Stir
in tomato sauce; add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer sauce while
you spread half the rice in the bottom of greased casserole;	cover with sausage mixture, then top with the final layer
of
rice.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, if you wish. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve bubbling hot.

title: bacon and pea casserole
directions: Add bacon pieces to peas, plus 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Add salt, pepper, white sauce and onion.
Place in greased casserole. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: dinosaur mud
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, melted butter and dash of cinnamon. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Allow to cool. Spread slightly thawed ice cream over cookies and freeze.

title: oil free muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix milk, egg and corn syrup together and blend with dry ingredients. Line muffin pans with paper cups and fill.
Divide equally.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Store in plastic bag to retain moisture.
Put in refrigerator after 3 days if there is any left over.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed for 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk (begin and end with flour).
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pantry reuben casserole
directions: Bring water to a rapid boil.
Add salt, if desired.
Add pasta; cook, uncovered.
Drain; rinse in cold water.
Add all ingredients.
Cook 45 to 50 minutes, then serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In making sauce, cook sugar, salt, flour, beaten egg, milk, mustard and vinegar over hot water in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Blend thoroughly and cool.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Blend butter or margarine with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla to butter and sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Add oats, chocolate chips and pecans.
Dough should be crumbly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Split hot dog buns and place face down in pan. Beat eggs completely.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour over buns and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Place 2 cups of strawberries in a large mixing bowl, set aside. Mash 1 c. of strawberries. Combine mashed and unmashed strawberries, sugar and cornstarch in a saute pan. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in strawberry juice, cover and chill. After thoroughly chilled, mix with remaining 1 c. strawberries.

title: tangy baked chicken
directions: Marinate the chicken breasts at least 12 hours in a mixture made from the cranberry sauce, onion soup mix and the French dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon stick rolls
directions: Cut crust off bread; roll flat.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar.
Spread mixture on bread; roll up bread (jelly roll style).
Dip in melted butter; roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture. Freeze before cooking.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; do not drain. Next, spread pie filling on pineapple.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pie filling.
Slice the stick of butter on cake mix.
Cut nuts in pieces and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cake will be soft.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: In
x 13-inch pan, pour hash browns.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese,
salt
and onion.	Pour over hash browns.	Top with crushed
corn
flakes
and	drizzle
with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend together.
Mix with potatoes or macaroni.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over ham, cheese and onions.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: orange-glazed chicken(with matzo-nut stuffing)
directions: Cook onion, celery and almonds in the 1/3 cup chicken fat until vegetables are tender.
Add coarsely crushed matzos or farfel; brown lightly.
In a large bowl, combine the chicken broth, egg, 1 tablespoon peel, salt and pepper.
Add matzo mixture and blend well.
Let stand 15 minutes to absorb broth.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook the frozen vegetables in about 3 cups of the chicken broth.
When done, add the chicken, both cans of soup, salt and pepper to your own taste.
(A good seasoning to use is Cavender's Greek seasoning).
You can use this instead of salt and pepper if you want to.
Bring to a simmering boil, add the two packets of soup mix.
Mixture should have a semi-thick broth.
Pour into a large casserole dish.

title: beer cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients, except beer, and beat with electric mixer.
Pour in beer slowly and beat until cheese is very smooth. Store in covered jar.
Remove from refrigerator at least 30 minutes before serving.
Beat once more.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Cook onion and pepper in a bit of bacon grease.
Combine all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice, soup and water in pan.
Place chicken on top, skin side up.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 60 minutes. Check once during baking.
If dry, add water.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots and when still firm, drain (about 10 minutes). Mix tomato soup and sugar.
Add vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper.
Beat and add oil.
Add vegetables and refrigerate.

title: frogmore stew
directions: In a huge pot, bring water and beer to boil.
Use twice the volume of water and beer to volume of ingredients.
Add at least 4 cans of beer (small sip from each is permitted).
Add 1/8 cup of seafood seasonings, salt, 1/4 cup of pepper and one box of crab boil and let water cook on low heat for at least one hour (approximately 3 gallons water).
Add sausage and boil for 6 minutes.
Add corn and boil 7 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 4 more minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add and stir in remaining ingredients. Chill and roll in a ball.
Roll in parsley flakes or chopped nuts. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: vegetarian pizza 1
directions: Roll out crescent rolls flat and bake according to directions (17 x 14-inch cookie sheet).
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and mayo and "frost" cooked dough.
Cut broccoli (tiny bite size) flowerets and place on cream cheese, along with sliced scallions and olives. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
(Better if made night before.)

title: squash pie
directions: Mix spices, salt and sugar into squash.
Add milk, then beaten eggs.
Pour into large unbaked pie shell and bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and then add sour cream, chili powder, corn and salsa.
Mix well until blended with a fork or spoon.
Break up about 3 cups of chips and sprinkle over mixture (after it has been placed in a casserole dish).
Then sprinkle the cheese on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour remaining chips into bowl and serve to the side.
Cut up the lettuce and add tomato.
Serve as a side salad to be mixed with casserole.

title: rich egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Put on floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up; cover.
Let rise until double in size, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans. Punch down dough, divide in half and place into pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled (1 hour).
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until loaves sound hollow when tapped.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter; add sifted sugar and cocoa, then add milk and vanilla.
Blend over low heat until smooth.
Add nuts.
(Do not cook.)
Pour into greased pan and place in refrigerator until hard enough to cut into squares, about 1 hour.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes in bite size pieces.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Return to low heat and add butter, salt and pepper.
Let milk warm and butter melt.
Add 2 tablespoons flour for a thicker sauce.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top of apples.)

title: chicken hot pot
directions: Saute leeks and garlic to soften.
Place cheese, wine, stock and 2 teaspoons corn flour in blender until smooth.
Put chicken on top of leeks, pour on cheese mixture.
Layer potatoes on top of mixture.
Cover with oiled piece of foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: baked onions parmesan
directions: Peel onions and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over onions.
Add salt and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mcfadden's flats
directions: Spray 10 x 13-inch rectangular pan with Pam.
Layer ingredients in pan in order given, lightly seasoning between each layer.
Pour warm, undiluted soup over all.
Cover with foil. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Combine all the ingredients together.
Make into balls about the size of a quarter.
Using 2 tablespoons oil brown on all sides.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Combine with vegetables.
Pour in salad dressing.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Stir before serving. Makes 8 (2/3 cup) servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soups, water and vegetables together in a roasting pan.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash (about 1 1/2 pounds) and onion (chopped) together until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain and mash.
Beat in eggs.
Add Cheddar cheese and mix.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square baking dish.
Spread broccoli in bottom of dish.
Beat eggs and sour cream together for 1 minute; pour over broccoli.
Top with tomato slices and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and knife comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma jo's irish puffs
directions: Set aside 2 cups flour.
In a large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat water, milk and margarine to 125° to 130°.
Stir into dry mixture.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make a soft dough.
On a floured surface, knead for 4 minutes. Put into a greased bowl.
Place the bowl in a pan of hot tap water.
Cover the bowl and let rise for 15 to 20 minutes. Divide in half and roll out on a floured surface. Cut into squares and fry in shortening or oil until lightly browned on both sides.

title: fruit cocktail pudding cake
directions: Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: oriental chicken
directions: In
large
saucepan
lightly
brown chicken in 2 tablespoons salad oil.
Add broth, rice, sherry, soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Bring to boil;
reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes more or until
done. Stir occasionally.
Stir 1/2 cup water into 3 or 4
tablespoons cornstarch
until
smooth.
Stir into chicken; cook, stirring until thickened.

title: bread pudding
directions: In
mixing
bowl
beat	together
milk,
eggs, salt and vanilla.
Stir
in	bread
pieces.	Pour
mixture into 1-quart baking
dish, greased.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Put 1-inch of hot water in larger pan. Set filled baking dish in it.	Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: eggless dip or sandwich spread
directions: Mix together well.
Delicious served in pita bread with alfalfa sprouts or lettuce.

title: fried (whole) turkey
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine the Italian dressing, garlic juice, salt, pepper, lemon juice and Worcestershire.
With a clean cloth, carefully strain the mixture and secure at least 1 cup of particle free liquid.
With a basting needle, shoot bird in all fleshy parts, especially breasts and thighs.
Try to use all of the marinade.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Beat egg until light and gradually add sugar.
Add marshmallows, milk and lemon juice.
Cook on surface at 200° until smooth and thick, stirring often.
Cool and fold in whipped cream. Pour over combined fruit and nuts; mix well.
Chill for 24 hours. Serve in lettuce cups.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Make pudding.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Crush up cookies.
Alternate layers of cookies and pudding.
Cookie layer on top.
Plant flower and gummy worms. Serve with trowel.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise, chile sauce, salt and pepper.
Add to egg mixture. Mix well.
Makes 4 cups.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in 1/2-inch thick pieces. Dip in buttermilk, then in a mix of 1/2 yellow meal and 1/2 flour.
Brown on one side; turn and brown other side. Dust with coarse black pepper. Serve at once with crisp bacon and chilled applesauce.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to
350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking
pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake	25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool thoroughly.
Then cut in squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tube pan.

title: bourbon-pecan bread
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg, beating well.
Combine milk and 1/2 cup bourbon.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups pecans and orange rind.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons bourbon.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: picante chicken casserole
directions: Heat oil and saute mushrooms and onion.
Stir in chiles and picante
sauce.
Cook
and	stir
over
medium
heat for 5 minutes.
In
a casserole, place chicken in the bottom.
Cover with all but
1/2 cup of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Combine rice, sour cream and 1/2 cup of the sauce and spread
over
chicken.
Sprinkle
on cheese and paprika.
Heat for 15	minutes more or until cheese melts.
Healthy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits (fourths).
Roll in mixture of sugars and cinnamon.
Toss in a Pam-sprayed Bundt pan.
Melt a stick of oleo; add remaining amount of mixture and pour over biscuits. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Invert pan.
(You may add nuts to margarine if desired.)

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat together sugar, syrup, salt, flour and eggs.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Turn rounded side of some pecans so they will look good.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for about 1 hour, or until filling is just set.

title: fruit dip
directions: Using a hand mixer, cream all ingredients together.
Add 2 to 3 dashes of cinnamon and mix well.
Serve with apple and pear wedges, pineapple spears or other fresh fruits.

title: wheat and tomato sauce
directions: Soak wheat in water to clean. (Wheat should absorb water.) Meanwhile, saute onion in oil on medium-high heat until onions start to brown.
Add tomato paste and 3 c. water.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and softened wheat. Cover and let boil stirring occasionally.
Boil until it starts to dry about 20 mins.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Let stand about 10 mins.
Serve.

title: spinach-parmesan dip
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate. Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hot sausage
directions: Cover sausage with water.
Simmer 2 hours.
Cut up onions and peppers in large pieces and saute in oil until soft.
Add tomato sauce and 2 cans water from sausage and simmer 1 hour.
Add sausage to sauce and simmer 1 hour.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with topping and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: best banana bread
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients, set aside. In a large bowl mix together sugar, eggs, oil and water. Add the dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in the nuts and bananas.
Pour into 2 medium loaf pans. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: veal baked in sour cream
directions: Brown veal in butter in skillet.
Transfer to baking dish. Saute the onion and mushrooms in skillet.
Stir in flour, water, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom sauce over veal. Cover.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and topping together with mixer.
Slice and dip apples in Fruit Fresh.
Drain. Serve.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, in mixing bowl; beat on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Stir in chopped pecans; pour into shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool.
For full flavor, cover and let stand 1 day before serving.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: This wonderful pie is so easy and delicious!
Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with slices of bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over bread.
Mix eggs, onion, sausage and milk (and optional items).
Pour over bread and cheese.
Place in fridge overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diabetic bars
directions: Cook dates, raisins and prunes in the 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Add margarine, cool and stir.
Add beaten eggs, flour, soda and vanilla.
Add nuts and cinnamon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom burgers(for vegetarians; doesn't really taste like mushrooms)
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Season with nutmeg, salt and cayenne pepper.
Place mushrooms in a mixing bowl with the beaten egg.
Add onion, green pepper and bread crumbs.
Shape into hamburger size patties.
Add more bread crumbs, if needed, to hold patties together.
Fry patties in a little margarine in a hot skillet.
Serve on whole wheat bread with melted Havarti cheese on top.

title: white fudge
directions: Toast chopped pecans for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt cream cheese in double boiler.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and toasted nuts.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter and marshmallow cream in a bowl and set aside.
Put sugar and milk in heavy saucepan.
Add butter; bring to boil and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add to mixture in bowl and beat well until thick.
Put in buttered pan and cool.

title: mom's blueberry buckle
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Put in greased 8-inch pan. Spread berries over batter and add 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, 1/3 cup flour and 1/4 cup butter.
Rub butter into dry ingredients, then sprinkle over berries.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion. Drain. Add soups, garlic salt, chili powder, salt, pepper, and half of cheese. Add drained spaghetti. Mix well. Spread remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until bubbly and browned.

title: tiramisu toffee dessert
directions: Arrange cake slices on bottom of rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inches, cutting cake slices if necessary to cover bottom of dish. Drizzle coffee over cake. Beat sugar, chocolate syrup and cream cheese until smooth. Add whipping cream. Beat on medium speed until light and fluffy. Spread over cake. Sprinkle with candy. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour, but no longer than 24 hours to set dessert and blend flavors.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine flour and cheese.
Cut in butter.
Add sauce and blend well.
Roll dough into long strips about 3/4 inch in diameter. Freeze 15 minutes.
Slice into thin wafers.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle wafers with different combinations of spices and seed.
Serve with apple slices.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; spoon half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool cake for 5 minutes.
While cake is baking, combine caramels, butter and condensed milk in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until caramels melt.
Spread over cake.
Spread remaining cake batter evenly over caramel mixture. Sprinkle pecans and chocolate morsels over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cake in oven for 10 minutes.
Cool; cut cake into squares to serve.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into each pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Good with ice cream.
The other pie can be frozen and served later.

title: spice muffins
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift with spices, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, sugar, shortening and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat only until smooth.
Fill well oiled muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: butter pecan turtle cookies
directions: Combine crust ingredients.
Mix at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes or until particles are fine.
Pat firmly into an ungreased 13-inch oblong pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over unbaked crust.

title: lemon bars
directions: Meanwhile, beat eggs well.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in flour and baking powder.
Pour over hot-baked crust.
Return to oven.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: five-pound fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and margarine in a heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Cook for 7 minutes after it starts to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour into a large mixer bowl into which has been poured 3 (6 ounce) packages of semi-sweet chocolate chips or butterscotch if you desire and marshmallow cream.
Mix with mixer until well blended.
Nuts may be added if you wish.

title: real vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook packages of vegetables separately, according to directions and drain.
Mix with water chestnuts and put in a 10 x 14-inch buttered casserole.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Store in the refrigerator for up to 1 week in airtight container or freeze for a month. Makes 1 cup (1/4 cup replaces 1 egg).
Per 1/4 cup contains 70 calories, 4 grams fat.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt shortening in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, eggs, the melted shortening from pan and the milk; mix until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped nuts with a fork and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 of the carton of Cool Whip and the 4x sugar.
Spread this over the cooled crust.
Mix the two boxes of instant pudding with the milk and add this as the third layer. Spread the remaining Cool Whip carefully over the chocolate layer. Garnish with shaved chocolate or chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours (or up to 2 days) before serving.
Also freezes well. Serves 10 to 12.

title: swiss chard - italian style
directions: *Hunt's Choice Cut tomatoes (14.5 ounce can) works fine; don't drain, use juice too.

title: swiss mushroom burgers
directions: Combine mushrooms and butter in 2-cup glass measure. Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until just about tender. Add water and cornstarch; mix well. Stir in bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens slightly, stirring once. Set aside. Combine ground beef, catsup, seasoned salt and pepper.

Mix lightly. Shape into 4 patties; place on microwave-safe roasting rack. If desired, brush with additional Worcestershire sauce. Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, rotating dish once.
Place bottom half of buns on microwave-safe serving plate. Top each with meat patty, mushroom sauce, cheese
slice and top half of bun. Microwave on High, uncovered, 45 to 60 seconds or until cheese starts to melt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: all-in-one-throw-in devil's food cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in greased square cake pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip or your favorite frosting.

title: wooey-gooey cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and press in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: salsa
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients and squeeze with lime juice. Serve with chips or fajitas.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion and egg.
Soften bread in the milk and add to meat.
Add salt and pepper and mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, onions and bacon.
In another bowl, combine mayo, vinegar, sugar and seeds for dressing.
Mix well. Pour dressing over vegetables; mix well.

title: sausage bread
directions: Place dough in bowl; cover.
Let rise 6 to 8 hours.
Cover 2 cookie sheets with foil.
In frying pan, place peeled sausages. Fry well and drain.
Add cheese; mix well.
Add egg, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well.
Let set in pan.
Cut dough in half.
Roll half into rectangle; place half of sausage mixture on one side of dough.
Fold over, pinch and seal open edge.
Shape into crescent on cookie sheet with pinched side on outside.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Make second crescent the same way.

title: polish sausage
directions: Mix ingredients and stuff in casings.
Steam-fry until brown. Cook about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: my grandmom's potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine celery, pickles, vinegar, mayonnaise and mustard.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, eggs, ham, salt and pepper. Toss lightly and refrigerate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: riviera rice pudding
directions: Pour rice into large pot of boiling salted water.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook exactly 7 minutes.
Add milk and butter. Stir a little.
Bring just to boil, lower heat, cover and cook slowly for 1 hour on low heat.
Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Pour into rice mixture, stirring slowly, until rice starts to thicken.
Serve hot or cold with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon sprinkled on top.
Topping gives it a browned look.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: peanutty crisscrosses
directions: In medium bowl, combine oats, flour and soda.
In large bowl, beat together margarine, peanut butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill dough about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough to form 1-inch balls and flatten.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Use tines of fork (or potato masher) dipped in granulated sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes about 4 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Whip heavy cream and cheese.
Combine with Miracle Whip.
Add drained crushed pineapple, cherries, lemon juice and marshmallows. Chill until ready to serve.

title: my mother's sweet potato bread
directions: Peel and grind sweet potatoes.
Stir in salt.
Add enough sugar until sweet to taste.
Add vanilla, stirring after each ingredient. Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add flour (enough to make a thick paste mixture).
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar, creaming well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put pie filling, then pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle butter over cake mix. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together cream and oleo. Add sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy. Stir in nuts. Frost cooled cake. Good on Green Apple Cake.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix until well blended and smooth.
Chill spread between buttered slices of bread.
Makes 1 cup.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cook eggplant, onions and celery in boiling, salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Add egg and cheese to celery, onions and eggplant.
Mix in crumbled Ritz crackers and soup.
Place in greased baking dish. Top with crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in pot and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix Tang, sugar, tea, cinnamon and salt. Mix 2 teaspoons tea to cup of hot water.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix margarine, eggs and vanilla. Add flour and sugar. Mix well. Add pecans, chocolate chips and coconut. Bake until doesn't shake in middle.

title: diabetic - brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat vigorously until well blended. Spread mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: refrigerated rolls
directions: Over shortening, salt and sugar, pour boiling water.
Blend and cool.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water and dissolve. Add 2 beaten eggs and mix well with shortening.
Add flour, blend well and cover.
Place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours overnight. Make into desired shape and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400°.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Have pineapple, cherry pie filling and milk very cold.
Drain pineapple; mix with pie filling.
Add milk and nuts.
Fold in topping and refrigerate overnight.

title: praline bars
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Melt oleo; stir in brown sugar and pecans.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and cool completely.
Easy, but oh so good!

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple-banana slush(low calorie)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.

title: green rice
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Saut onions in butter. Layer in casserole: rice, spinach, onion, cheese (reserve 3 tablespoons), salt and pepper. Repeat about 3 times. Sprinkle reserved cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream enchiladas(mexican)
directions: Oven bake tortillas until soft.
Make filling.
Mix soup, sour cream and chilies.
Coat baking dish with filling.
Put filling in tortilla shell.
Sprinkle in green onion and both cheeses.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.

title: breakfast lasagna
directions: Layer French toast, ham and cheese.
Top with apple pie filling and granola.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with topping.

title: apple dip
directions: Spread cream cheese
on
a
serving plate.
Put caramel topping on cream
cheese.
Sprinkle
pecans
on top. Chill the apple dip for about
1 hour. Slice your apples and dip them in your apple dip.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Combine strawberries, lemon rind and juice in saucepan. Simmer 10 minutes.
Put through a food mill or sieve or liquefy in blender.
Cool.
Pour fruit mixture over large block of ice in punch bowl.
Add sparkling Burgundy, champagne and Sauterne. Garnish with whole strawberries and lemon slices, if wished. Makes 35 punch cup servings and is guaranteed to put a little punch in your anniversary.

title: peach sugar-free pie
directions: Drain the peaches.
Add pudding mix, sour cream, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: curry dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order given; beat until well blended.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Mix and heat for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan, mixing well. Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: baked cod fillets
directions: Put tomato slices in bottom of baking dish.
Dip fillets in milk and arrange on top of tomato slices.
Spread crumb mixture on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll to size of a walnut.
Dip in cold water and then in sugar to form a glaze on top while baking.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: peppers, potatoes and so on
directions: Core and cut peppers into wide strips; wash and remove all seeds.
Peel and dice or thickly slice potatoes.
Peel and slice onions.
Cut steak into cubes or bite size pieces.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Fry pepper alone until tender; add all other ingredients and spices.
Fry all together until all are evenly cooked.
Drain oil and serve.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack raw okra into hot pint jars.
Add 1 hot pepper and 1 garlic bud to each jar.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, salt and celery seed; pour over okra in jars.
Seal with hot lids.
Let stand 10 days before serving.
Chill before use to insure crispness.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream cheese and sugar well.
Blend in vanilla and egg.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheesecake.
Put back in oven; bake 10 more minutes.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, salt and nuts. Spread half the mixture in a 7 x 11-inch buttered pan.
Spread apricots over this to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Spread remaining batter over preserves and bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: potato soup
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add.
Place flour in large bowl; add dates, candy and nuts.
Stir well and add to cream mixture.
Add coconut.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Mix orange juice and powdered sugar; pour over top of cake and let stand overnight.

title: cauliflower, pasta and chickpea soup
directions: Heat oil in a 3 to 4-quart pot over medium heat.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes or until onion is translucent.
Add cauliflower and cook 2 more minutes.
Add broth, water, tomatoes, pasta and chickpeas.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until pasta is firm-tender.
Season with pepper.
Garnish each serving with fresh basil and grated Romano cheese.

title: cola roast
directions: Combine salt, pepper and garlic powder; rub over surface of roast.
Brown roast on all sides in vegetable oil in a Dutch oven. Drain off drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours or until tender. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix together. Spray casserole dish first. Dot in margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add bouillon cubes.
Drain and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine beef and onion; cook until beef is brown.
Add tomato sauce and water. Cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Spoon over noodles. Blend sour cream, mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Pour over meat mixture and bake 15 minutes longer in 400° oven.
Add grated cheese and bake five minutes longer.
Serves a lot.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries. Combine with sugar and place in colander to drain overnight.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt together the first 3 items and pour over remaining ingredients.
Mix in a large pan or bowl.
Pack in Pam sprayed angel food cake pan.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from pan.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: prune cake and sauce
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs in a mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed of an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and set aside.

title: doris' pineapple casserole
