directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then pineapple, then bread cubes.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix lime and water.
Add cucumbers.
Let soak for 24 hours. Rinse cucumbers and soak in cold water for 4 hours.
Change water every hour.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil. Turn fire off and add cucumbers; cover and let stand overnight. Next morning, bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut 2 (15 x 12-inch) pieces of heavy duty aluminum foil; place a chicken breast in center of each.
Top with onion and remaining ingredients.
Wrap well.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 servings; 1.8 grams fat; 221 calories; 66 mg. cholesterol.

title: wonder salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well.

title: cheese and ham casserole
directions: Place cubes of bread, ham and cheese in Pam sprayed 2-quart casserole.
Mix slightly.
Mix remainder of ingredients in blender or with mixer until well mixed.
Pour over top.
Make day before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 1 hour.

title: oreo torte
directions: Mix together and press in pan.

title: oven dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients in a heavy Magnalite-type pot with a lid. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, keeping the pot covered.
Do not peek!!!

title: brenna's favorite breadsticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
On medium speed with electric mixer, beat in honey.
Gradually add 3 cups flour.
Add remaining flour to form soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth (about 10 minutes).
Cut into 4 equal sized pieces of dough.
Form each piece into 5 ropes about 10-inches in length. Arrange on greased baking sheets about 1-inch apart.
Let rise in warm place for 15 minutes.
Brush each rope lightly with butter and sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 20 breadsticks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Double for 2 pies.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, salt, pepper and onion in skillet.
Pour off grease.
Combine sour cream and cream of mushroom soup in a bowl.
Fill flour tortilla shells with 2 tablespoons ground beef mixture.
Cover with 1 tablespoon sour cream and soup and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Fold shell over and place, folded side down, in 9 x 13 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Repeat until all tortilla shells are filled.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into large casserole, 3-quart size.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lucille's turkey salad
directions: Alternate as you grind turkey, celery, pickles and eggs.
Add mayonnaise to mixture after ground.
May use less or more mayonnaise, if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: south of the borders
directions: Pat hamburger meat into patties.
Fry until done.
Heat up chili and toast slices of bread.
Peel the potatoes and slice for homemade French fries.
Deep fat fry potatoes.
Dice onion.
Put 1 or 2 slices of toast on plate.
Lay hamburger patty on top of toast.
Lay 1 slice of cheese on top of patty.
Pour chili over cheese and bread.
Sprinkle onion on top.
Salt fries to taste. Serve hot.

title: chicken a la pam
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon olive oil and add leeks and garlic.
When leeks are slightly transparent, add sun-dried tomatoes and red pepper.
Add salt and pepper, Parmesan and cream to finish the sauce.
Serve over cooked pasta.
This is a quick and easy recipe.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and chill overnight to blend flavors.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cookies 'n cream pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and crushed cookies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: flaky pastries
directions: Combine flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening and butter until crumbly.
Mix vinegar with 5 tablespoons cold water.
Add flour mixture and stir with fork until dough clings together. Divide into 2 portions.
Roll on floured surface.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until just soft. In large oven-safe pot or casserole, combine all ingredients, including potatoes.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until potatoes are completely soft and cheese is melted.
Sauce should be thickened (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken breast in broth and water at least 1 hour.
Remove from heat and let cool to skin, bone and dice (bite sized).
Add all ingredients to soup.
Add okra, cut in bite size pieces.
Cook sausage meat (in small pieces) and add flour to make a roux.
Add to soup.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Add rice last 15 minutes.
If too thick, add another can chicken broth.
If too thin, add more rice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popped popcorn and pecans on cookie sheet.
Boil butter, salt, brown sugar and corn syrup for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn. Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring it every 15 minutes.
Let cool before eating.
Bake until crispy and dry.
Can add peanuts.

title: old fashion sponge cakes
directions: Mix the sugar to the eggs and beat 15 minutes.
Sift in the flour mixed with baking powder and salt. Add flavoring and mix gently.
Put in a muffin pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal jumble bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except preserves; mix well. Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of pan.
Spread preserves over base to within 1/2 inch of pan's edge. Sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten a bit.
Break bread into small pieces.
Mix bread and vegetables together.
Add milk and margarine.
Mix slowly, stirring to moisten bread.
Don't make it too wet.
If you use more milk, scald it first.
Divide bread mixture into 4 parts, putting one part on each breast half.
Wrap chicken around bread mixture.
Place in greased casserole or baking pan, seam-side down.
Cover.
Add a little water to pan. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until chicken slightly browned.

title: fast cabbage burgers
directions: Saute ground beef and onions.
Add salt, pepper, allspice and cabbage.
Add 2 cups water and simmer 20 minutes, stirring often. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain excess fat.
Mix in soups and enchilada sauce.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, alternate layers:
tortillas (cut into quarters), hamburger mixture and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Put marshmallows into hot water with jello.
Let sit until melted after stirring.
Add cold water and stir, then let set in refrigerator until just slightly jelled.
Beat until light and add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Beat in mayonnaise and pineapple. Pour into mold and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: lime ice cream dessert
directions: Freeze for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: aunt thelma's cranberry sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix water and sugar; stir to dissolve sugar. Bring to a boil.
Add cranberries, return to boil.
Reduce heat. Cool at room temperature and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add other ingredients except rice and cheese. Bring to a good boil. Add rice.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Put in casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in a 350° oven and let cheese melt.

title: au gratin stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub and dry potatoes.
With an apple corer, remove a cylinder from the center of each potato.
Fill each cavity with cheese.
Seal ends with tiny pieces of cylinders which have been removed.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until tender, about 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Saute onions in butter, then add hamburger, garlic salt, salt, sugar and pepper.
Simmer together about 3 minutes.
Add sour cream and tomato sauce.
Prepare biscuit mix according to directions on package.
Roll dough onto flour mixture.
Cut into 8 squares (about 5-inches).
Place 1/3 cup mixture on each square and fold diagonally to make triangles.
Seal edges; prick top and brush with butter.
Bake on sheet at 400° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with favorite sauce.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Crush Oreos finely.
Mix with melted butter. Spread on bottom of a 9-inch pan. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and condensed milk until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix 1/2 cup chocolate chips with flour until completely coated.
Shake off extra flour.
Mix chips in batter. Pour batter onto cookie crust. Sprinkle remaining chips on top of batter. Bake 1 hour.

title: lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain noodles according to package directions.
Wrap sausage around cheese and wrap in lasagna noodles.
Place in baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans together and pour out onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until solid; then roll in chopped pecans.

title: party cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and make in small balls.
Flatten with your thumb.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and egg until creamy.
Mix in flour mixture alternately with cold water.
Mix in soda and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes or until done.

title: 5-minute coffee cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to cream mixture; mix until smooth.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, vanilla, half and half and condensed milk; stir real good.
Add mashed bananas.
Pour into freezer can of churn.
Fill with whole milk the rest of the way to the line.
Ready to churn.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put oats, sugar, lard and salt in a bread mixer.
Pour over them the boiling water.
Let cool.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add white flour, enough to make stiff ball.
Turn until ball holds its shape, take 6 to 8 cups flour to start with.
Add more if needed as dough is sticky after rising.
Makes 3 loaves, 1 1/2 pounds each.

title: island chicken
directions: Put all ingredients together, except chicken in glass baking dish.
Mix well.
Add chicken and toss lightly.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours. Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Take foil off during last 10 minutes. All liquid will be absorbed into the chicken.
Serve hot or cold.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Stir.
Top with chips. Bake 5 minutes more or until hot.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: luscious lemon cream
directions: In bowl, beat together eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice. In saucepan, combine remaining sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened; remove from heat. Gradually beat in egg mixture.
Ove low heat, cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add vanilla; cool.
Fold in whipped cream. Serve with fresh fruit.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 3 cups.

title: pull apart rolls
directions: The night before, butter well a Bundt pan.
Put in 1 cup nuts. Place frozen rolls, about 16 to 18, evenly in pan on the nuts. Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over.
In a saucepan, melt butter. Mix in cinnamon and brown sugar; drizzle over rolls.
Set aside, covered, to sit unrefrigerated overnight.

title: fried venison and noodles(wild game)
directions: Cut venison into serving-size pieces.
Tenderize on both sides; salt and pepper to taste and coat with flour.
Heat oil in skillet; brown venison on both sides.
Cut up onions and brown; add celery, if desired.
Add Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, until tender; add a little water, if necessary.
Cook noodles; drain.
Pour venison mixture over noodles and stir together.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onions, celery and carrots until golden and soft.
Add potatoes and broth and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add mace and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cream.

title: mandarin orange whip(quick and refreshing!)
directions: In medium bowl, combine whipped topping and yogurt; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in orange sections.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Garnish with macaroon crumbs.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: good and easy beef stew
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large covered casserole dish and cook 4 to 5 hours at 275°.

title: coconut icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add extra powdered sugar for thicker icing.

title: low calorie divine pudding pie(serves 4)
directions: Mix and press into pie pan.

title: baked carrots
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine the butter, shortening, brown and white sugars, egg, vanilla, flour, baking soda, chips and nuts and mix well.
Drop by the tablespoonful onto a lightly greased baking pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 2 to 4 dozen.

title: steak & potatoes casserole
directions: Mix steak with flour, salt and pepper, coating it thoroughly. Fry in oil and remove. Keep 2 tsp of dripping and add beef bouillon and steak sauce to the drippings. Bring the liquid to a boil, Simmer for 1 minute and remove from heat. Layer all ingredients in a 3 1/2 quart baking dish, (13 x 9). Cook approx. 2 hours at 350 degrees, or until potatoes are tender.

title: good pickles
directions: Bring to boil vinegar and water, drop in cucumbers.
Let heat through and pack in sterilized jars.
Fill with vinegar mixture. Add to each quart jar 2 saccharin tablets (whole grain) and 1 teaspoon salt.
Seal.

title: texas egg gravy
directions: Lightly brown flour in baking drippings.
Beat eggs in a bowl and add milk, water and eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add to flour and bacon drippings.
Stir until it thickens.
Serve with biscuits.
If too thick, you can thin with water.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over meal.
Stir constantly.
Add butter. Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, baking powder and salt.
Bake at 350° in a greased baking dish for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Combine cake mix, milk and pudding. Beat with a spoon (do not use a mixer). Pour into greased sheet pan. Sprinkle butterscotch morsels and pecans evenly over cake. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt in medium bowl; set aside. Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl. Add dry ingredients and mix. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 1 (9 x 13) pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar until blended well.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add jello and water.
Next, add flour and mix until well blended.
Add strawberries last.
Pour cake into prepared pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add milk and vinegar together, then cocoa and water together.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done in prepared pan.

title: frosted sugar cookies
directions: Beat with mixer:
sugar, oil then eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin, works well to keep refrigerated in between baking times.
Bake 8-10 minutes at 400° on top shelf.

title: "bourbon sauce with pecans"(ice cream topping)
directions: Cream 13 ounce = 52 large, 6 1/2 cup miniatures.

title: tomato and green pepper salad
directions: Broil peppers in an oven for several minutes, turning them 3 or 4 times, until the skin blisters.
When cool enough to handle, peel, seed and chop them.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: chicken with rice (arroz con pollo)
directions: Cut chicken and season it to taste with Adobo.
Add ham with oil and fry for 3 minutes.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, olives and oregano; fry for 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup water; add chicken and cook for about 10 minutes.
Stir once.
Add rest of water and salt. When boiling, add rice and stir once.
When it starts boiling again, turn to medium temperature until all water is absorbed. Stir rice, reduce to low temperature, cover it and cook rice for 20 minutes.
Stir once again and cook for 15 minutes or until done.
Buen Provecho! (Enjoy!)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and use 6 tablespoons of water in recipe.
Mix all ingredients. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cookie sheet should be greased or sprayed with Pam.

title: fruit cremes
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Set aside.
Combine orange juice and ice cubes to make 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O.
Stir until melted.
Add milk.
Pour in dessert dishes.
Chill.
Soft set in 30 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix oats, flour, margarine, brown sugar and pecans and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until crisp.
Halve the mixture and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour 1/2 of bottle caramel over mixture.
Defrost ice cream and spread softened ice cream over caramel.
Sprinkle about half of mixture over ice cream, pour remainder of caramel over this and freeze.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients with beef.
Cook until macaroni is done.

title: easy salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple and keep.
Mix juice and pudding mix together.
Add cherries, pineapple and oranges. Store in refrigerator.
Before serving, add sliced bananas to mixture.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine or butter, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet. Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup; add cream cheese and gelatin.
Mix until cheese and gelatin are dissolved.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to cool mixture.
Pour into a greased mold and chill overnight. (Use a 3 1/2-cup mold.)

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: peach bread
directions: Puree in blender the peaches and 6 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Combine and set aside the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon.
Cream together 1 1/2 cups sugar and shortening.
Add and mix well the eggs.
Add peach puree and dry ingredients and mix well until the ingredients are moistened. Stir in vanilla extract and pecans.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Note:
Eleven ounces of dates will do.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix hamburger, onion and spaghetti with Ragu sauce.
Layer in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish the hamburger and spaghetti mixture and cheese. Repeat this procedure.
Top with cheese.
Put under broiler until cheese is melted and brown.

title: white cheese ball
directions: Mix together in food processor until ball forms.
Put on plate and decorate with olives.

title: kugelhupf
directions: Scald the milk and pour over the butter, sugar and salt, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Then stir in
the yeast, lemon rind and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add the flour, raisins and stiffly beaten whites.
Stir until well mixed. Let rise until double in bulk, then beat thoroughly and pour into a tube pan, which has been greased well and dusted with flour and blanched almonds arranged on bottom.
Cover with a towel.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes. Continue baking at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove from pan; sprinkle with powdered sugar immediately.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Grind ingredients coarse and press out fluid.
Add coarsely ground ingredients to mayonnaise.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with sliced Granny Smith apples.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: Mix lard, flour, and salt until crumbly. Add enough water to make dough soft. Roll and cut. Makes one crust.

title: potato chip munchies
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter with electric mixer on medium speed until softened.
Add the 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
With mixer on low speed, gradually add potato chips until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten dough with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: date bars
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates and soda in small bowl; mix and cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add the eggs, vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Then add the flour alternately with the date mixture and beat well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350°.
You may substitute 1/2 cup whole wheat flour for 1/2 cup white flour. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: veal parpakush
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add to bacon fat 1 tablespoon shortening, onion and garlic.
Fry until golden brown. Add salt, pepper, paprika, veal and bacon.
Brown together.
Add 1 cup water, green pepper, mushrooms, tomato and parsley.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 hour.
When meat is tender, add flour and blend well.
Add sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with spaetzie.

title: old-fashioned tea cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add 2 cups of sugar; beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and gradually add it to the creamed mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with extra sugar. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Measure all dry ingredients and sift together.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix together by hand.
Bake in greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool before removing from pan.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan over low heat (or in microwave), melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Add crushed cookies and chopped pecans; mix well. Press half of mixture firmly in greased pan.
Reserve rest for topping.
Combine cream cheese, egg, vanilla and sweetened condensed milk in medium bowl.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy. Pour into crust-lined pan.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars. Makes 36 bars.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix and form into small balls, 1 inch.
Melt large piece of white chocolate (enough to coat all the balls) and 1/4 of 1 piece of rectangular paraffin.
Dip each ball into melted mixture and place on wax paper to dry.

title: peanut butter brittle
directions: Combine first three ingredients and let come to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Let boil to hard crack on candy thermometer.
Then add soda, butter and vanilla.
Mix quickly and pour onto buttered foil and spread as cools.

title: emily clyburn's recipe for a family favorite - chinese chews
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Blend in flour.
Pat mixture onto greased cookie sheet and bake in moderate (350°) oven for 15 minutes.

title: corn slaw
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Press firmly in bottom of 2 (9-inch) pans.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Use firm, but ripe peaches.
Pare thinly.
Mix vinegar, sugar, stick cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Add peaches and boil gently until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Pack in hot sterile jars. Add hot syrup to within 1/4-inch of top, then seal.
Makes 2 quarts.
Chill before serving.

title: mushroom medley
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; wash and dry. Combine bacon. Blend cream cheese and milk. Mix in bacon and chives. Stuff mushrooms. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crush chips and line 9 x 13 baking dish.
Brown ground beef, add beans, corn, and taco seasoning.
Mix well and pour over top of chips in baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave on Medium for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Combine flour and salt.
Combine sour cream and soda.
Add alternately to creamed mixture.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in large, greased and floured tube pan.
Makes a large cake.

title: beet wine
directions: Wash beets, but do not peel them.
Cut up in slices and add boiling water.
Bring back to a boil and simmer until tender. Strain with a sieve or cheesecloth.
Add sugar and cloves to juice and heat to dissolve sugar.
Stir all the time.
Cool until lukewarm.
Put in a bowl or crock.
Spread yeast on a slice of toast and place on juice.
Cover for 3 days, then remove toast. Strain and bottle.
Cork and bottle loosely at first.
Add one piece of hard sugar candy to each bottle in 4 or 5 days.
Ready in 6 months or more.

title: no excuse bread
directions: Put first 8 ingredients into mixing bowl with 3 cups flour. Beat 5 to 10 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in another 3 cups flour.
Knead rest of flour in.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes. Cover with plastic wrap and folded towel.
Let rest 20 minutes. Punch down and divide into 2 equal parts.
Roll each part into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Roll up.
Shape and place in greased pan. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
About 10 minutes before baking, remove from refrigerator and preheat oven. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: snickers bar
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle Grape-Nuts on top.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into 8 bars.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Mix nuts and coconut together.
Spread over pie shells.
Next mix sugar, eggs, cocoa, butter, vanilla and milk.
Do not boil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot cranberry compote
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and lemon juice; toss well.
Pour into lightly greased, shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over fruit.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and sprinkle over top of fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be dessert or side dish at meal.

title: pie crust for fried pies
directions: Sift flour and salt in mixing bowl.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until it looks like meal.
Mix egg and milk together.
Add to dry mixture and mix well.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours to chill.
Can be kept in refrigerator several days in sealed bowl.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Chop onions in food processor.
Scoop out avocados.
Add to onions.
Process until well blended.
Add lemon juice and blend. Pour mixture into pie plate.
Pour sour cream over guacamole, making certain all green is covered.
Pour taco sauce over sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Serve with taco chips.

title: garden stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Pierce potatoes.
Place in microwave for 12-15 minutes.
Slice off the top of potato.
Scoop out pulp. Heat small skillet, adding onion, drained broccoli, salad dressing and pulp.
Mix well.
Brush potato skin with oil.
Spoon mixture into shell and place on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy french bread
directions: Add yeast and sugar to warm water, letting yeast set and bubble.
Add 2 eggs and 1/4 cup oil, mixing well.
Add flour until at the kneading stage.
Knead until it feels spongy.
Let rise until double.
Divide in half and roll into long French loaves. Place on cookie sheet; let rise.
Brush with butter and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and butter top again.
Cool on wire rack.

title: coffee crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening into crumbs.
Take out 2 cups for top crumbs.
Add beaten eggs to remaining crumbs.
Add spices and sour milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Put one cup of crumbs on bottom of greased pan.
Add mixture and remaining crumbs on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water.
Spoon into well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until done.

title: cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites good; mix cream of tartar, then add sugar. Add vanilla.
Crumble the packages of saltines in and mix well with chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until light brown, about 1/2 hour.
When it cools, spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hamburger and bean casserole(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion and drain.
Fry the bacon crisp and crumble when cool.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook all day on low.

title: gramma morris's hardtack
directions: *Rye flour may omitted by adding more white flour.

title: quick mix yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add all biscuit mix, mixing well.
Turn onto floured board; knead well until smooth (about 10 minutes).
Form into rolls; put in greased baking pan.
Cover; let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put margarine on top when they come out of the oven.

title: boneless round roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all seasonings and garlic in small bow; mix well.
Cut some small incisions in roast; fill slits with seasonings.
Heat oil in large ovenproof casserole over medium heat.
Add meat and sear on all sides; season with salt and pepper.
Remove meat from casserole and set aside.
Add vegetables to casserole and cook 5 minutes.
Incorporate beef stock and tomato paste; mix well, then return roast to casserole.
Season with salt, cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours in oven.
Fifteen minutes before end of cooking time, pour in the sherry wine. Serve with assorted steamed vegetables.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well.
Best if mixed the day before.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar, oil and pumpkin together well in a large mixing bowl; then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans (3 loaf pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 8 x 9-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Test for firmness with a toothpick.

title: heath bar pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until slightly browned.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Crush 8 Heath candy bars.
Sprinkle most over mix, reserving about 1/4 cup for top.
Mix pudding mix according to directions on box and spread over the Heath bars.
Sprinkle remaining Heath bars on top of pudding.
Chill.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In a casserole dish lay broccoli spears on bottom of pan. Pour all remaining ingredients into a bowl and mix together.
Then take your chicken and cut up into pieces.
Mix chicken and all your ingredients and pour on top of broccoli.
Then prepare your stuffing, place on top of the mix.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and butter and remove from heat.
Add condensed milk, flour, vanilla, salt and eggs and mix well.
Reserve 1/4 cup coconut.
Stir in remaining coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with remaining coconut.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until top is firm and coconut is slightly browned. Cool to room temperature.
Cut and serve.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until knife comes out clean from center of pie.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add next 6 ingredients to butterscotch mixture.
Mix well.
Fold chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts to mixture only until combined, about 5 strokes.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center will be jiggly but becomes firm upon cooling.
Recipe can be doubled, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: korean broiled flank steak
directions: Marinate, covered, overnight.
Broil 5 minutes per side, placing onions over meat.
Serve with rice.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour with baking soda and add to butter mixture a little at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla; blend until smooth.
Fold in softly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in an uncooked pie shell. Chip butter on top.
Cook until firm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put all ingredients together in baking dish and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: swedish meatballs for two
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Saute 3 tablespoons chopped onion in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Strain.
Mix onion with meat mixture. Form small balls and brown on all sides in hot fat.
Remove meatballs and put into another pan.

title: dorito pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
In medium bowl, mix taco sauce, enchilada sauce, chiles and soup together.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees, covered for 90 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms; save liquid.
Add enough hot water to mushroom liquid to make 1 cup.
Add bouillon cube.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
Add flour.
Gradually add liquids.
Cook until it thickens on top of stove.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh lumpia (eggrolls)
directions: Soak anatto in cooking oil.
Set aside.
Saute garlic in vegetable oil until brown.
Add onions, pork and shrimps.
Pour in soup stock and cover; cook over medium heat until pork is tender. Add sweet potato, potatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Then mix the rest of vegetables.
Strain asuete oil to the vegetable mixture. Season with salt or fish sauce.
Cook until all vegetables are done.
Cool in a colander while allowing liquid to drain out. When cool, wrap in Semex lumpia wrappers with leaf of lettuce showing at one end.
Serve with lumpia sauce.

title: microwave quick strawberry jam
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe bowl combine strawberries and powdered pectin; mix well.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture comes to full rolling boil, stirring every 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until mixture comes to full rolling boil, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Continue to boil for 1 minute.
Skim foam.
Spoon into 4 clean, hot 8-ounce jars; screw lids on firmly.
Cool several hours.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or in freezer up to 3 months.
Makes 4 cups.

title: dip for tortilla chips
directions: Brown beef and sausage, drain thoroughly. In crock pot mix soup and milk, add cheese. Cook until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally, then add meat. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend oil and shortening together with electric mixer.
Add sugar, then egg and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Sift flour with soda, cream of tartar and salt and add to creamed mixture. Chill dough.
Form into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass that has been dipped in granulated sugar.
Dip glass in sugar each time before flattening the cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix together Seven Seas dressing and McCormick Salad Supreme. Mix all together and marinate overnight.

title: banana creme delight
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine cornstarch and water.
Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla; cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas and dip in lemon juice; drain.
Arrange on bottom of crust.
Pour filling over bananas and cover bananas with filling.
Chill 4 hours, until set.
Spread whipped cream on top.
Slice remaining banana; dip in lemon juice.
Drain and arrange on top.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, seasonings and bouillon in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook on medium for 15 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup milk with flour until smooth.
Add flour mixture, remaining milk and butter to potato mixture.
Cook over medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly.

title: blackened red fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Measure thickness of fish.
Combine onion powder, garlic powder, white pepper, red pepper, black pepper, thyme and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Brush fish evenly on both sides with melted margarine.
Coat fillets on both sides with pepper mixture.

title: cole slaw
directions: In food processor, slice cabbage, using a very thin blade. Grate carrots.
Cut onion into very fine pieces.
Slice pepper into thin slices.
Mix ingredients together.
Add dressing.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least several hours before serving.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in order.
Crumble bacon over and cover with plastic wrap.
Let stand refrigerated overnight.

title: crispy herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray jelly roll pan with vegetable spray.
In medium bowl, combine first 7 (dry) ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Dip chicken in water; roll in potato flake mixture to coat.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all together
and put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cracker delight
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, nuts and raisins together over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put 1 teaspoon on crackers.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Let cool. Spread Cream Cheese frosting on top.

title: apple cider
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Mix the apple cider, orange juice and lemon juice together.
Add and boil mixture. Serve cold or hot.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Brown meats and onion; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Core cabbage; steam cabbage a few minutes, just to tenderize leaves. Mix meat, rice and kraut.
Gently separate cabbage leaves.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon meat mixture into each leaf.
Roll up; place in baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 300°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk thoroughly; then fold in whipping cream (whipped).
Add lemon rind.
Pour into crust and chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken bog
directions: Boil chicken with onion and soup mix.
Pick chicken off bone. Add rice to broth; cook 15 minutes, then add chicken and smoked sausage.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until lightly fluffed.
Gradually add flour; beat until smooth.
Pat mixture into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pick with tines of fork evenly over surface to eliminate air bubbles.
Bake in oven on Full power for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: donuts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let cool to lukewarm, while dissolving yeast in the warm water.
Mix all ingredients and add 4 cups flour; mix well.
Knead in 2 more cups flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Grease top of dough.
Cover with towel.
Keep in refrigerator until 2 hours before time to use.
Take out of refrigerator and cut out donuts.
Let rise.
Cook in hot shortening.

title: chili
directions: Make a paste of salt, sugar, flour and chili powder.
Brown beef; add onions, celery and simmer until tender.
Add tomatoes and soup; cook 15 minutes.
Then add the paste.
Mix well and let simmer about 1 hour, stirring frequently, to avoid sticking.
Add beans, cook 15 minutes longer.

title: corn fritters with corncob syrup
directions: Beat egg in a medium bowl, just enough to mix.
Mix in corn, salt, flour, sugar and butter.
Beat until well blended.

title: three bean pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
In a large bowl, mix oil, vinegar, onion, red pepper, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper until blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat and chill.

title: easy escalloped eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Mix eggplant, croutons and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Put in a lightly buttered casserole dish.
Combine milk, flour and seasonings; pour over eggplant mixture.
Top with remaining cheese; dot with butter.
Cover; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover; continue baking for an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Mix all cans with meat mixture and simmer on stove top.
Layer mixture with Doritos in casserole dish.
Put in oven at 400° until bubbly.
Remove and top with cheese.
Return to oven and melt cheese.

title: aunt nancy's pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Pie is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: smothered quail
directions: Salt and pepper quail; roll in flour.
Brown slowly in fat. Prepare rice.
Place quail in a baking dish; mound rice in center.

title: peachy fruit punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; add 2 cups cold water.
Pour in gallon container; add pineapple and orange juice. Add cold water to fill container.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: eggs in a nest
directions: Cut a circular hole, about the size of a jelly glass, in each piece of bread (center).
Butter or Pam the griddle.
Lightly butter one side of each piece of bread and place on griddle, butter side down.
While bread is toasting, butter the top side.
When bread is toasted on bottom, flip over and carefully break egg into each hole; fry until egg is set and toasted on bottom side.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, mixing thoroughly.
Add cinnamon, zucchini, vanilla and nuts.

title: low-fat citrus chicken with peppers(14% calories from fat)
directions: Microwave Directions:
Place chicken breast halves in 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) microwave-safe dish.
Arrange bell pepper strips around chicken.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the soup, margarine, cheese, mayonnaise and eggs until smooth.
Add broccoli and onion.
Pour the mixture into a medium sized casserole and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together well and save 3/4 cup of crumbs to put on top of cake.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in baking pan with crumbs on top.

title: grape nuts
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake it, grind it, toast it and eat it with milk.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up chili roll and mix everything together.
Heat through until hot or bake in oven.
Also works good in a heated casserole dish or crock-pot.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, tomato juice, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add beef, bread crumbs and parsley; mix well. On a piece of heavy-duty foil, pat meat mixture into a 12 inch x 10 inch rectangle.
Place the ham and shredded cheese on loaf to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Roll up, jelly-roll style, beginning with the short end and peeling foil away while rolling.
Place on a greased baking pan with seam side down; seal ends.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Top with sliced cheese; bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: charlie bread
directions: Coat sides of pan.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: italian icing
directions: Boil flour and milk together, making a paste.
Allow to cool. Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and whip.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Bring to boil sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes and then add cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Beat (with wooden spoon) quickly.
While still hot, drop mixture onto a cookie sheet.
You can make cookies any size you wish.
Let cool for 5 minutes and serve.
(No baking!!)
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: raisin-peanut popcorn balls(yield: 8 to 10 balls)
directions: Combine popcorn, raisins and peanuts in a large bowl.
Mix both sugars, water and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil without stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour syrup over popcorn mixture.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Butter hands and form quickly into balls.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil together.
Add well-beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix until smooth. Add chopped nuts and grated carrots.
Bake in one (9 x 12-inch) pan for about 45 minutes or 3 greased (9-inch) layer pans at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries in bowl.
Sprinkle sugar on top and let stand, then stir sugar in berries.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Mix jello. Let stand until jello begins to thicken, then mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator until real thick.

title: hidden cheeseburgers(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on top of rolls.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until light, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar until sugar dissolves. Soften gelatin in cold water. Stir gelatin into pineapple mixture. Add lemon and cherry juices to the mixture. Set aside to cool. Mash cream cheese and cut cherries. Mix cherries and cheese with pineapple. Whip the cream and fold into fruit mixture. Pour into greased mold.

title: cheese-scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of water until just glossy. Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; add cheese, stirring until melted. Spoon potatoes in baking dish;
arrange onion over potatoes.
Pour cheese sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Take about 3 or 4 tablespoons of fat; put in a skillet.
Add rice; stir often until rice is brown. Add chopped onions while rice is browning, if desired.
Add tomatoes and some broth of chicken.
Add cup at a time, until rice is done and not too dry.
Add chicken; cook 15 or 20 minutes longer.

title: aunt ethel's homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Add yeast and water; stir well.
Knead on floured paper until ready to cut into rolls.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Butter before baking.

title: holiday dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Chop cabbage and green onions.
Add chicken breasts, toasted almond and sesame seed.
Break Ramen noodles in small pieces.
Put all in large Tupperware-type bowl.
Mix oil, vinegar and other ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over cabbage mixture and stir well.
Cover and leave in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Brush bottom and side of crust with egg yolk. Bake on baking sheet until light brown. Combine apples, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well and spoon into crust. Mix remaining flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle topping mixture evenly over apples. Bake on baking sheet until topping is golden and filling is bubbling.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water; stir until jello is dissolved. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold or refrigerator-safe bowl and congeal until firm.
Great for Thanksgiving dinner or any time with fresh pork.

title: raspberry custard pie
directions: Make one pie crust; don't bake it.
Put raspberries in pan with crust.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 300° for 45 minutes.
Knife inserted at center comes out clean when custard is done.

title: green bean and hamburger casserole
directions: Mix the flour very smoothly with four tablespoons of the milk. When this is well mixed, add the remainder.
Cut up the rabbits into joints.
Put them into a stewpan with the milk and other ingredients and simmer them very gently until quite tender.
Stir the contents from time to time to keep the milk smooth and prevent it from burning.
Half an hour will be sufficient for the cooking of this dish.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream 2 cups
sugar
and butter until smooth.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift
flour.
Sift
together
flour, baking powder and soda.
Alternate the sour cream and flour mixture into the creamed mixture; stir
in
the
vanilla.
Pour
1/2 the batter into a greased
x
9-inch
pan.
Combine
remaining sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Pour
part
of the topping on batter in pan.
Pour rest of
the
batter
into the pan and top with the remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve out or in the pan; stays fresh
in the pan and will not fall apart as much.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw hamburger in a large oblong, greased pan. Add onion and soup undiluted, the Tater Tots. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Prepare ground beef as for tacos.
Add seasoning mix as directions say.
Place lettuce on plate, then layer of chips, layer of meat mixture, onions and top with cheese.
Arrange tomatoes on top.
Serve immediately.

title: bertha's spicy bean cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in beans.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Fold in apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients; mix well. Press firmly into a loaf pan or in an iron, greased frying pan. Bake for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour and 3 spices.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and oil. Make a hole in middle of dry ingredients.
Add oil mixture, applesauce, nuts and/or raisins, baking soda, powder and water. Mix well.
Place in greased, raised loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes one loaf.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together well and shape into meat loaf.
Place in
baking dish and cover top with ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: west virginia blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add to sugar and butter mixture.
Mix flour, buttermilk, spices, soda and baking powder thoroughly.
Then add blackberries.
Bake in three layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix milk and mayonnaise.
Whip until smooth.
Set aside. Combine chicken and other ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour milk and mayonnaise mixture over all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking casserole.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix 1 1/2 heaping tablespoonfuls with 1 cup hot water (more or less to taste).

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Drop a dab into a cup of cold water.
If you can form a ball with your fingers, it is ready.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until it's starting to thicken.
As it cools, it will get thicker.
Pour over cake that is in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
This is great on the Fresh Apple Cake.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: In a large pan, brown meat with onions.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Stir in cabbage and water. Simmer 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Goes well with corn bread.

title: mary's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, soda, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, no longer.

title: tennessee fried cabbage
directions: Place salt pork in a large Dutch oven; cook, uncovered, over medium heat 15 minutes or until salt pork is browned. Add chopped cabbage; cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes. Add salt, stirring well. Cook, uncovered, an additional 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Serve immediately.

title: morrilyn's first prize chili
directions: Heat oil in large stock pot.
Brown onion, pepper, trip tip and garlic.
Add spices and sugar.
Saute about 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, red chili sauce and drained tomatoes.
Simmer over low heat about 2 hours.
Add drained beans, corn and olives. Simmer about 1 more hour.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with a whisk until smooth.
Fold in topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk in bowl.
Beat with whisk 1 to 2 minutes (it will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk.
Mix well.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 8.

title: chicken stew
directions: Pressure cook chicken in 3 quarts water for 45 minutes. Drain, cool, debone and chop.
Cook diced potatoes, onions, corn and margarine in broth about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes (chopped), tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, back pepper, salt and chopped chicken.
Cook over medium to low heat until onions and potatoes are fully done.
Stir frequently while cooking.

title: fish barbecue
directions: Saute onion in Wesson oil.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream
oleo,
Crisco
and
sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well. Sift
flour,
soda and salt;
add small amount to first mixture. Add
milk, vanilla, nuts and coconut, then remaining flour.
Mix well and fold in egg whites that are beaten stiff. Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 3 to 4 layers.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix first 3 ingredients; Pat into 9 1/2 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: rich mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Place in a greased 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Melt 4 Tbsp of butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and sugar until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.

title: joe's penuche fudge
directions: Mix sugars, flour, butter and milk; boil until a soft ball may be formed in cold water, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from stove. Cool.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 1 cup of walnuts.
Beat until creamy and pour into buttered pans.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheesy sourdough bread
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese, onions and garlic in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread on cut surfaces of bread.
Sprinkle top with parsley.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil until bubbly.
Cut into slices.

title: turkey breast and corn bread dressing
directions: Sprinkle salt on turkey breast.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add water and bouillon cubes to celery and simmer until celery is tender.
Combine bread crumbs, sage, oregano and thyme.
Add celery mixture and eggs; mix well.
Add more water, if necessary.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: kentucky fried corn
directions: Lightly fry bacon, mix other ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into bacon grease.
Fry slowly so as not to brown too quickly, about 25 minutes, or until done.
(Peppers and pimentos can be omitted.)

title: don't cook the manicotti
directions: In a skillet, brown meat with onion and garlic powder.
Stir in half of tomato juice (2 cups), tomato paste, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash together sweet potatoes, sugar and pineapple.
Take a large marshmallow and put potato mixture around it, using your hands.
Roll in coconut.
Place in buttered dish and bake at 320° for about 20 minutes.

title: preacher cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When cool, store in cookie jar.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: For dough, mix box cake mix, stick of oleo and egg into a soft dough. Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. For filling, beat cream cheese, 3 eggs, and box of confectioners sugar until smooth. Pour over the dough mixture. Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes or until light brown. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat until almonds are coated with sugar.
Place lettuce, romaine, celery and onion in plastic bag.
Pour dressing into bag.
Add oranges.
Shake until mixed well.
Add almonds before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Fill large kettle 2/3 full of water. Add vegetables, 1 Tbsp. salt and onion. Boil for 30 minutes. Add velveeta cheese cubes, instant potatoes and Coffee Mate. Stir continuously until melted and creamy. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crust ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli; combine onion and oil in saucepan and heat. Add broccoli; cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; heat to boiling point. Keep stirring; reduce heat and stir in Cheez Whiz and milk.
Add salt and cook few minutes more.
Add rice and stir.
Bake in buttered casserole (covered) at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and honey together.
Add oil.
Mix baking powder, soda and flour.
Add warm water and mix at low speed.
Pour into a 10 x 12-inch oblong baking pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Very good.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Add
all these ingredients together.
Do not cook.
Put into a 5 quart ice cream freezer.	Freeze until very firm.

title: rice, broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: After sauteing onion in butter, mix in soup and cream.
Stir in rice, which has been cooked, and large jar of Cheez Whiz.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425°, covered, then for 20 minutes uncovered.

title: jalousie cherry tart
directions: Thaw puff pastry sheets 20 minutes.
Unfold and roll 1 sheet on a lightly floured surface to a 9 x 14-inch rectangle.
Trim edges.
Put on a large baking sheet and prick at 1-inch intervals. Spread preserves over pastry leaving a 3/4-inch border all around.
Turn pastry border over edges of filling, sealing corners with egg-water mixture.
Brush pastry with more egg mixture. Roll second pastry sheet to make a rectangle slightly larger than the filled pastry sheet and trim.
Fold in half lengthwise and slash through folded edge to make cuts about 2 1/2-inches long and 1/4-inches apart.
Open pastry and place on top of cherry filling. Press edges with the tines of a fork to seal and brush top pastry with egg-water mixture.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 400° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer until browned.
Transfer to wire rack and cool.
Serves 10.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk, margarine and sugar until soft ball stage (240°). Stir frequently; burns easily.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and then peanut butter until melted and smooth.

title: red clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter and oil, then add oregano, basil, cayenne pepper and parsley.
Add the minced clams with the juice and the large can of tomato puree.
Simmer for 1 hour.
This recipe doubles and triples easily.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Scramble and fry sausage in large skillet.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add milk, grated cheese and pepper.
Then add sausage to egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: herbed asparagus
directions: Melt margarine; add seasonings.
Add asparagus and mix until asparagus is coated.

title: environmentally correct drain unclogger
directions: Pour in order down drain and let set overnight.

title: snack mix(ultra low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Slice bagels into small rounds.
In a large bowl, combine bagel rounds, all cereals and pretzels.
Mix hot water with Molly McButter and pour into small spray bottle, if available.
It is possible to sprinkle the water and butter mixture, but spraying is better.
Alternately spray and then sprinkle Ranch dressing mix on cereal mixture in large bowl. Spray a little on top; sprinkle Ranch dressing mix and a few sesame seed.
Toss cereal mixture.
Repeat spraying and adding dressing mix and sesame seed until all required amounts are used.

title: artichoke appetizer spread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
May be served warm or cold. Serve on crackers.

title: holiday pudding
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon and salt.
Add this to creamed brown sugar and butter.
Add alternately with milk.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into hot syrup in baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Especially good.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until clear.
Add strawberry gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add sliced strawberries and pour in pie pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Refrigerate.

title: microwave quiche
directions: Microwave bacon on High until crisp, about 9 minutes; crumble. Combine cheeses with onion and bacon.
Sprinkle mixture in a lightly greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Combine milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat on high 1 minute.
Pour over bacon and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave on Medium-high for 18 minutes.
Rotate dish twice while cooking.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Divide in half.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place beef in 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with celery, carrots and onion. Combine soup and water. Pour over meat and vegetables. Cover and bake in 350° oven 1 1/2 hours; add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: fresh start punch
directions: In blender, put sugar, spices, eggs and orange juice.
Beat well.
Pour into 1/2 gallon container and add pineapple juice. Stir and chill.
Add ginger ale and sherbet when ready to serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Can use any other raw vegetables you select.

title: raspberry cream cheese bars
directions: Mix oats, flour, 2 cups of
sugar, coconut, nuts, butter and brown sugar until crumbly.
Save 2 1/2 cups of mixture.
Pat rest in pan; bake 20 minutes.
Spread jam.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Simmer beef with water, salt and pepper, covered for 1 hour. Skim off fat.
Simmer, covered for 3 hours.
Remove meat from bone.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Combine mashed potatoes and vanilla with enough confectioners sugar to form a fondant the consistency of pie dough (the amount of sugar is much less important than the consistency).
Chill; divide the dough into 3 sections.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick between two pieces of waxed paper.
Spread with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up from short side (jelly roll fashion). Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Keep in cool place. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Clean, slice and cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Slice the onion and green pepper thin.
Mix soup, oil, vinegar, salt, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Mix well and drain before serving with slotted spoon.

title: southern-style shrimp and rice
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove from skillet, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Drain bacon on paper towels. Cook and stir bell peppers and onions in reserved drippings until tender.
Stir in rice, pepper, hot pepper sauce, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Crumble bacon.
Add bacon and shrimp to skillet mixture; heat thoroughly.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Use 1 pint of lime sherbet for each 2 liter Sprite.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage; let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Add celery and green pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool and pour over cabbage. Freeze in serving portions.
Thaw at room temperature for about 2 hours before serving, cutting through with a knife.
Serve slightly frosty.

title: mama's banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas.
In large dish, make layers with bananas, then wafers.
Set aside.
In double boiler, combine sugar, flour, milk, 1 egg and 3 egg yolks.
Boil until thick.
Pour over layers.
Beat egg whites with mixer until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat well.
Top pudding and brown under broiler.

title: peanut butter crunches
directions: Mix 1/2 cup cereal with peanut butter and honey.
Form into 24 small balls and roll in remaining cereal.
Chill.
Can use cornflakes instead of Grape-Nuts cereal.
Yields 24.
Serving 1 (exchanges 1/2 starch/bread, 1 fat).

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger with chopped onion and drain.
Mix ketchup, sugar, mustard, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce together with hamburger.
Add water and corn flakes.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick spiced nut bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with cooking spray of your choice (I use canola).
Mix all ingredients well and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets thoroughly.
Boil until tender; slip peelings off. Cut, if needed.
Place in jars.
Add salt, then brine.
Seal jars. Heat in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: apricot glazed leg of lamb
directions: Insert garlic slivers into surface of meat.
Rub with oil, salt and pepper.
Roast in preheated oven at 400° over 15 minutes per pound for medium size roast (approximately 150° internal temperature).
During the last 30 minutes of roasting, brush roast with glaze.

title: turkey-vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook veggies according to directions in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook onion, celery and thyme until onion is tender.
Add soups and milk; stir until smooth and add turkey, veggies and pepper.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Unroll and lay unseparated crescent rolls across top of mixture or cut to form a lattice top.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: becky's hot sauce
directions: In large pot, cut up onions and only cut stems off jalapenos. It depends on how many jalapenos you use as to how hot you want it. Add the water and boil until onions and jalapenos are soft, approximately 15 minutes. Drain water. Add tomatoes, garlic, salt and cilantro. Return to heat for approximately 15 minutes. Remove and put in blender to chop up. Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: cinnamon-chocolate brownies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa in a medium mixing bowl; stir well.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture beating well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon half of batter into a greased 8-inch square pan, spreading evenly. Combine brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon in a small bowl; stir well.

Sprinkle brown sugar mixture evenly over batter in pan. Spoon remaining batter over brown sugar mixture, spreading evenly. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and instant pudding together.
Add crushed pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well and pour into a 7 x 11-inch Pyrex dish and refrigerate.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, but crisp.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine next 3 ingredients, pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese; combine bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle all over.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked bean combo
directions: In a Dutch oven, fry bacon slices until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels; crumble.
To bacon drippings in pot, add onions, sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar;
cook on medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add all beans and crumbled bacon; mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in crock-pot, cover and cook on LOW for at least 4 hours.
Cook last 20 minutes uncovered.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Rinse in cold water and drain. Brown meat in butter and add salt and pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, chopped onions and noodles.
Alternate layers of noodle mixture and meat mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Begin with noodles and end with meat mix.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift baking powder with 1 cup flour.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Use additional flour to make dough of right consistency.

title: easy spoon bread
directions: Mix eggs, milks, salt and butter; add soda last.
Pour into buttered baking dish (2 to 2 1/2-quart).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve at once.
Will fall like a souffle.
Will serve 8.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add eggs, oleo and zucchini.
Mix and drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° until done.

title: tater tot bake
directions: Saute ground beef with onion.
Layer ground beef with green beans and Tater Tots in baking dish. Combine soup and milk and beat with an egg beater.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: confetti fettuccine
directions: In large high sided saute pan, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil. Add chicken strips and saute, stirring constantly until chicken pieces whiten, 1 to 2 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove chicken from pan and set aside.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces and place in the bottom of a deep bowl.
Drain peas and place in a layer on top of the lettuce.
Chop the green onions and add on top of the peas. Next, add a layer of bacon bits.
Next, add ranch salad dressing.
Add a layer of shredded cheese and top with a layer of chopped egg.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle steak with meat tenderizer, garlic salt and pepper. Brown in oil.
Add onion and cook until onion is tender.
Pour soup and can of water over steak and simmer about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cream potatoes or rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix bread crumbs with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix all ingredients and shape into one large loaf or two small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Cook chopped cabbage and celery until tender.
Add all ingredients together and simmer a couple of hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll into little balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into a large greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon into Pyrex baking dish.
Sprinkle with some grated cheese.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes (until sides boil and top starts to brown).
Serve with sturdy crackers (such as cracked wheat squares).

title: potato salad vinaigrette(serves 4)
directions: Scrub the potatoes and peel them if desired.
Place in a 3-quart saucepan with cold water to cover.
Bring to boil and cook about 20 minutes or until easily pierced with a skewer but not mushy.
Drain, rinse with cold water and slice thinly.
Place in a large bowl.
Toss gently with parsley and herbs.
In a small bowl, whisk together the vinegar, lemon juice, mustard and garlic. Slowly whisk in the oil.
Pour the dressing over the warm potatoes. Toss lightly to coat the potatoes with the dressing.
Let cool. Add the onions or celery and toss well.

title: noodle beef casserole
directions: Mix the first six ingredients together.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add sour cream to noodles.
In a greased 9 inch x 13 inch dish, layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture.
Mix the 3 cheeses together and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: oriental skillet
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in rice, broth, water and soy sauce.
Cover.
Simmer until rice is done, about 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chickpea spread
directions: In
using
canned chickpeas, drain and rinse under cold running
water until water runs clear.
Spread on paper towels and pat
dry.	Freshly
cooked chickpeas need only be drained and cooled.
In
blender,
place chickpeas, salt, garlic, 1/2 cup
oil and 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Blend at high speed for 10 seconds. Stop
and
scrape
down
sides
with rubber spatula. Blend	again at high speed, adding as much oil as you need to prevent blender from clogging.
The finished mixture should be a very smooth puree, just thick
enough to hold its shape in a spoon.
Taste for seasoning.	Add
more salt or lemon juice if you like.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup (not diluted), add gelatin and the rest of the ingredients.
Heat and stir until well mixed and heated.
Pour into a mold and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: ice cream bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press half of mixture in bottom of 9x9 pan as a crust.
Flatten.

title: nutty artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in shallow pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serve with Air Crisp crackers.

title: cowboy sourdough starter
directions: Put water in crock, add yeast and sugar to soften, stir in flour.
Cover with a clean cloth.
Let rise until mixture is light and slightly aged, about 2 days.
Mixture will thin as it stands; add flour as needed.
As you use sourdough from the crock, replace it with equal amounts of flour and water.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly.
I put buttered Ritz crackers (crushed) on top just to cover.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs and margarine and press in bottom and sides of 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: pecan bar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Cut into squares.
Place pecan half on each bar.

title: mashed sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Peel,
clean
and slice potatoes 2 inches thick.
Place in pot and
boil for 30 minutes.
Add peeled and cored apples to
the potatoes and boil until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes and apple mixture to a smooth texture.
Add salt, butter, eggs and milk. Bake
in a greased baking pan for 20 to 25 minutes. A delicious side dish.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: peach or apple recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with sliced peaches or apples.
Pour flour mixture over top of fruit. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and cold water in small bowl for 5 minutes. Add sugar to boiling water in pan and stir a few minutes to dissolve some of the sugar.
Add sugar mixture to egg yolks and beat 5 minutes, changing to larger bowl when necessary.
Add lemon extract and vanilla.
Add cake flour to mixture and beat hard several revolutions of bowl.
Beat egg whites until foamy and then add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold into cake mixture.
Bake in 10 inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 275°, place cake on lower rack and turn oven to 325°.
Bake at this temperature about 25 minutes, then turn oven to 350° and finish baking.
Bake cake 1 hour 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade chocolate cake icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer for at least 3 minutes or until icing becomes creamy.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until soft; drain and cool potatoes. Mash.
Add sugar, flour, cream and eggs, then add nutmeg and melted butter.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then put on topping of marshmallows and brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zippy beef olive spread
directions: Soften onion in the sherry.
Blend the cream cheese with the mayonnaise.
