Mix with the onion.
Stir in the chopped beef and chopped olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: debbie's chicken cheese vegetable soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes, celery, onions, potatoes and water; cook 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables; cook 30 minutes.
Add soup and stir to blend.
Add cheese and chicken.
Stir to melt cheese.
Heat to taste.

title: grilled turkey breast on summer greens
directions: Place mustard in a bowl and slowly add the oil in a steady stream.
Whip constantly to create an emulsion.
Whip in the vinegar and lemon juice.
Add the garlic and the fresh herbs. Place the turkey breasts in the marinade and let sit overnight.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Rub with garlic and thyme.
Brown in hot oil in nonstick skillet.
Combine 2 tablespoons reserved juice with cornstarch.
Combine honey and mustard; stir into skillet with remaining juice.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: bob's sausage gravy(scaled for 12 servings)
directions: Brown sausage in 4 quart heavy aluminum pot breaking up into desired
consistency (some like it chunky).
Remove meat from fat and
add
margarine and all peppers to fat, stirring until liquified and well mixed.
Reduce heat to medium and add flour; stir
constantly
until
mixture bubbles and begins to turn almond color.
Replace sausage meat, mix well and immediately
add evaporated	milk.
Stir
well to prevent sticking. When mixture thickens, begin to add whole milk gradually until mixture
no longer
thickens and bubbles begin to appear.
At this time
the gravy is done;
however, the taste is enhanced if you cover it and let it simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rich, moist brownies
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Grease 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate, butter and shortening together over hot water.
Mix thoroughly; let cool slightly.
Beat eggs with salt until light.
Add sugar gradually and beat until creamy.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla, blending well.
Add flour all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Bake for 50 minutes or until food pick comes out clean when tested. Texture should be soft and moist.
Cut into small squares while hot.
Delicious topped with ice cream or I like to make an extra batch, wrap them in foil and freeze.
They are like fudge when they thaw.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, green chilies, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, 1 jar salsa, chili powder, oregano, cumin and parsley flakes.
Stir and let simmer 10 minutes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Dip tortillas in remaining jar of salsa and fill with 2 or 3 Tbsp. meat mixture. Roll up and place in pan.
Take remaining mixture and place around the sides of pan.
Pour salsa on top and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft; add mushrooms. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and red pepper; cook until shrimp are tender. Add flour and let thicken. When ready to serve, add sour cream and heat.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli; cook until tender. Blend in Cheez Whiz and chicken soup; stir until cheese is melted. Add rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbling good.

title: toasted triangles
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Mix all ingredients.
Toast bread lightly on one side, spread other side with mixture, then slice into triangles.
Place on tray and put into freezer until frozen, then put into plastic bags.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in a skillet; saute onion and celery until tender.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Split breasts in half and cut crosswise.
Cut drumsticks and thighs apart.
Put into 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add onions, carrots, celery, chicken broth, salt, bay leaves, pepper, thyme, lemon juice and 3 cups of water.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls as directed on tube except place them flat on 2 cookie sheets and press together to eliminate seams.
Cool.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh fruit. Makes 2 cups.
Can use other flavors also.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Wash onions.
Set aside to drain.
Take 2 paper towels and place slice of ham on one towel.
Blot dry with another towel. Spread ham with cream cheese.
Place onions on long edge of ham. Roll ham and onion to other side.
Slice with sharp knife, approximately 1/2-inch wide.
Arrange on platter.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and gelatin.
Add boiling water and other ingredients.
Mold overnight.

title: italian anise cookies
directions: Combine and whisk eggs, sugar, anise and vanilla flavorings. Add and mix well 4 cups of flour, salt and baking powder.
Add roasted almonds and mix.
Form into 4 loaves and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Slice and spread both sides with melted butter and rebake for 5 minutes on each side.

title: creamy chicken noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water; reserve.

title: yogurt dip
directions: Mix together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Line large Pyrex baking dish with foil.
Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Into a small bowl, combine balance of ingredients except rice and stir.
Pour ingredients over chicken.
Cover top of baking dish with foil.
Put in 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 45 minutes until golden and bubbly.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cool and debone.
Save broth.
Make up dough as for biscuits. Roll out.
Put into the pot of boiling broth. Put as many dumplings as it takes. Cook until tender, then layer a row of dumplings and a row of chicken, about 3 rows, in baking dish.
Cut margarine and place over top.
Roll dough as in dumplings. Cut into strips. Crisscross over top. Cook only until slightly brown.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In Bundt pan, freeze a big pan of punch mixture.
When ready to serve, put frozen punch ring in bottom of punch bowl and pour remaining punch over top.
Float lemon and orange slices on top.

title: brownies
directions: In small saucepan,
melt oleo.
Add cocoa; mix well and set aside to cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar, then vanilla and mix well. Add the cocoa mixture.
Add 1 cup pecans that have been coated with 1/2
cup
flour.
Pour
into
greased
and floured baking dish.
Bake
at
for
about
20 minutes in 8-inch square pan or 6 x 10-inch pan.

title: spiced tea
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add spices in metal tea ball or in cheesecloth.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tea bags and simmer 5 more minutes.
Add juices and heat or put in jars and store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, salt, 1/2 can tomato sauce, onion, egg and pepper.
Form into loaf pan.

title: squirrel under pressure
directions: Salt and pepper squirrels to taste and roll in flour.
Brown squirrels in fat until golden brown.
Remove from fat, then add all remaining ingredients, except Worcestershire, soup mix and water. Cook seasoning until vegetables are tender.
Add squirrels, Worcestershire, soup mix and water to seasoning and cook in pressure cooker.
After pressure cooker starts "giggling", cook for 18 minutes over medium heat.
Serve over rice.

title: light fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture begins to lose its glossiness and pour into buttered dish.

title: easy-do meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, onion, cracker crumbs and pepper.
Mix well. Add beef broth and mix until thoroughly blended. Turn into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake and icing
directions: Bring to boil oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking soda and cinnamon in a bowl.
Add melted oleo, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Spread on a cookie sheet.

title: pineapple mousse
directions: In a small pot put the gelatin and pineapple juice (extracted from can of pineapple chunks).
Bring it to a quick boil.
Remove from the stove.
Beat the egg whites to a fluff.
In a bowl put all egg yolks; add sugar.
Mix, then add gelatin mixture, condensed milk and egg whites.
Mix well, then add pineapple chunks.
Place in refrigerator until it thickens.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Make into balls and dip in chocolate.
Roll in coconuts or crushed nuts.

title: health salad
directions: Drain all cans of vegetables well.
Mix the first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Bring oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to a boil; pour over ingredients.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Best served the next day.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Split the squash in half.
Scoop out seeds.
Place each half on aluminum foil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add pat of butter, 1 teaspoon brown sugar, pinch of nutmeg and chopped nuts. Seal and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sardine stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Mash.
Blend egg yolks with remaining ingredients to form a smooth like paste. Stuff yolk-sardine mixture into halved egg whites.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: venison skillet dinner
directions: Melt fat in heavy skillet.
Add meat, garlic, parsley and onion; brown slightly.
Combine tomato paste, water, sugar and pepper.
Add to meat and mix.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add noodles, cover and cook until noodles are tender.
Serve with cheese.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Remove crusts from bread and butter.
Mix together chicken, eggs, olives, mushrooms, onion and mayonnaise (add a little more mayonnaise if needed).
Make sandwiches.
Lay in a greased pan, not quite together.
Mix together chicken soup and sour cream (add a little more sour cream if needed).
Pour sauce over sandwiches. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix the above ingredients and pour into a casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350
45-60 minutes.

title: dream pie(makes 3 pies)
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple, flour, sugar and jello until it thickens.
Stir all the time so it won't burn.

title: saucy baked pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and melt in skillet, enough to get 2 tablespoons fat.
Remove trimmings.
Broil chops in fat (hot). Season with salt and pepper.
Drain excess fat.

title: macaroon bars
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, flour, oil and almond extract. Spread mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 to 3/4 cup coconut with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle over mixture and press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Cut while warm.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add oil and mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add pumpkin last.
Bake at 350° in 3 (8-inch) layer pans for 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water as directed on package.
Combine mushroom soup, milk, tuna and noodles.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake in greased 1 3/4 quart casserole for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a 12 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown.

title: pineapple glazed apple pie
directions: In
a
large saucepan combine 1 1/4 cups pineapple juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil; add apple wedges.
Simmer covered 3
or 4
minutes
until
apples are tender but not soft.
With slotted spoon,
lift
apples
from juice.
Blend the remaining pineapple juice
with cornstarch.
Add to hot pineapple juice. Cook
and stir until thickens and bubbles.
Cook 1 minute more. Remove from heat;
stir in butter, vanilla and salt.
Cover and cool
30 minutes
without stirring.
Pour half of mixture into pie
shell, spreading to cover bottom.
Arrange apples on this. Then
rest
of mixture.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil sugar, water and spices for 5 minutes.
Add tea bags and allow to steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags, add cranberry juice and apple juice.
Serve hot.

title: praline bars
directions: Lay crackers
flat
in jelly roll pan.	Bring sugar and butter to	boil.
Boil
2	minutes.
(Do not boil longer.) Add nuts and spread
mixture
over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut when slightly cool.

title: gladys beach's different apple pie
directions: Pare apple and slice thin.
Add sugar mixed with flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Toss to cover.
Place in pie shell and top with margarine.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mixture may be stored in a tightly closed container.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very good served with ham.

title: cream torte
directions: Put in deep pie pan.

title: grandma's best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure the rum is of the highest quality, pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon thugar and beat again.
Open the second quart, if necessary.
Add 2 arge leggs, 2 loose with a drewscriver.
Sample the rum again, checking for tonscistity.
Next sift 3 cups of pepper or salt (it really doesn't matter).
Sample the rum again.
Sift pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 babblespoon of brown thugar or whatever you can find.
Wix mell. Grease the oven and turn cake pan to 350 gredees.
Now pour the whole mess into the oven and ake.
Check the rum again, and bo to ged!

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute meat with onion until meat is browned.
Combine remaining ingredients. Bake in covered casserole (3-quart size sprayed with Pam) at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: ritz cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, add sugar baking powder, and vanilla. Bake in a 9 inch pan for 45 minutes at 350 degrees. Let cool, top with whip cream. Put in refrigerator for 4 hours before serving.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Stir in garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Combine onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Place half of noodles in 2-quart baking dish.
Spread with half of cream cheese mixture and then half of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and top with Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven just to melt cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: austin's blue ribbon peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer or spoon.
Drop onto cookie sheet; sprinkle with some sugar and press with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Quick and easy cookies.
Great for kids to make.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch one-crust pie as directed on package. Beat eggs slightly with rotary beater. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean. Cool. Serve with Honey-Ginger Cream.

title: orange dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake at 325 degrees for one hour or longer.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar after the cake is cool.

title: shortribs debbie's style
directions: Place shortribs on broiler pan.
Broil until well browned to remove excess fat.
Transfer to slow cooker.
Saute onion in butter until limp and golden.
Pour in ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Heat until blended.
Pour over ribs.
Cover. Cook on low setting 8 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon oat lacies
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well. Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350° and remove dough from fridge.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until edges are light golden brown.
Cool one minute on sheet, then transfer to wire rack and cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco well.
Add buttermilk.
Mix with fork and beat; pour out on wax paper that has been floured.
Knead and pinch off; roll in palm of hand.
Makes 7 to 8 biscuits.
Easily doubles.

title: easy punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add orange juice, the juice from the lemons, cold water and pineapple juice.
Chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 25.

title: apple butter
directions: Add cider on start.
Then add sugar and spices when apples are cooked up good.
Cook slow on low heat.
Makes 18 pints.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour. Add milk, egg yolks and salt. Cook over medium heat until thickened. If it becomes lumpy, keep stirring until lumps are gone. Add margarine and vanilla. Cool. Pour into pie shell.

title: mexican tortilla casserole
directions: Prepare in all-in-one tube pan.

title: applesauce cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Use applesauce sweetened at it is for the table.
Cream butter and sugar.
Cut fruit and mix with 1 cup of flour.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: snowy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Mash potatoes with electric mixer; add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth.
Stir in chives.
Spoon into greased 10-cup casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon or tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except the oil in a bowl. Form mixture into patties. Cover and refrigerate for 1-3 hours. Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat to 350°. Cook patties 3-4 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Keep in low oven (175°) to warm until ready to serve.

title: gail's congealed cranberry salad
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan, drain pineapple into measuring cup; add enough water to make one cup; add 2 additional cups of water for a total of three cups of liquid. Add 1/2 can cranberries and marshmallows. Bring ingredients to a boil; add jell-o, stirring until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a 9 x 11 Pyrex dish. Chill well before serving.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, dip chicken into egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet over medium-low heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes, until browned on both sides and no longer pink. Remove.
Keep warm.
Pour off fat.
In skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water.
Heat through, stirring. Serve over chicken with rice or noodles. Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut vegetables and beef into medium sized pieces.
Do not brown meat.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and cook.
The longer it cooks, the better the taste.

title: new england seafood chowder
directions: In large Dutch oven place fish and enough water to cover. Cook over medium heat until fish flakes with a fork.
With a slotted spoon remove fish and break into bite-size pieces; set aside.
Measure cooking liquid and add enough to equal 4 cups. In the liquid, cook celery, onion and potatoes until tender. Combine flour and water to make a paste.
Stir into chowder.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Add fish, clams (with liquid), shrimp, crabmeat, salt, pepper, butter, milk and pimento.
Heat thoroughly, stirring.
Garnish.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and sift dry ingredients together.
Add mashed bananas to creamed mixture, then add flour and nuts.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: browny chews
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, salt and soda. Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in greased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan; cut in squares.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix cream, sugar and oil together.
Blend in eggs.
Add alternately dry ingredients with shredded carrots.
Grease and flour three 6 x 3-inch pans.
Bake one hour in 325° oven.

title: zenobia bryant's barbecued deer ribs
directions: Boil deer ribs	in
water until tender; drain water off and place ribs in baking pan and apply barbecue sauce lightly. Bake in oven at low heat until
brown
and	serve
with
slaw, baked or mashed potatoes or baked beans.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Scald, skin, cut into pieces and drain the tomatoes.
Chop onions, garlic, hot peppers and sweet peppers in blender.
Cook everything until thick, then cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: party thirst quencher
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water; do not refrigerate.
Chill juices and ginger ale.
At serving time, combine gelatin mixture, chilled juices and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Top with small scoops of sherbet.
Makes 32 punch cup servings.

title: spanish steak
directions: Combine ground chuck, chopped onion, egg, crumbled bacon, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place meat mixture on lightly greased foil forming into 2 oval loaves 2-inches thick.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: beef cheese balls
directions: Let cheese soften, then put in bowl.
Add onion and corned beef (loosen beef with fork).
Mix together and chill.
Form into balls.

title: library paste
directions: Mix cornstarch with cold water into a thick paste.
Add this paste to boiling water and stir over heat until the mixture becomes translucent.
Allow to cool.
Store in a covered container and use as a general purpose paper and craft paste.
This is nontoxic and completely safe for kids' craft projects.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the ice cubes in a blender. Whirl until smooth.
Bananas may be frozen in their skin, just peel the skin when you are ready to use them.
The skin will turn black in the freezer but it will not effect the flavor of the banana. Yields 4 servings.

title: maple-mustard glazed pork roast
directions: Stir together maple syrup, mustard, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper. Spread evenly over pork and place in a shallow pan. Roast in a 350 degree oven until internal temperature reaches 150 degrees. About 45-85 minutes. remove from oven and let stand ten minutes before slicing. (Also great made with chicken.)

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Place one piece of chicken at a time and shake to coat.
Brown chicken in oil, about 20 minutes.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Mix soup with 1/4 cup sherry wine and 1/4 teaspoon tarragon vinegar.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend in blender well. Add a little milk if necessary. Refrigerate.

title: no-bake strawberry dessert
directions: Arrange cake cubes in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish. In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in strawberries. Pour over cake and gently press cake down. Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour. In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened. Spoon over gelatin layer. Spread with whipped topping. Refrigerate until serving. Yields 20 servings.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Slice desired number of cukes lengthwise with green peelings on. In a mixing bowl, beat egg and milk with salt and pepper. Using a heavy, deep skillet, pour oil or shortening. Heat hot; our Fry Baby's aren't hot enough. Mix flour and cornmeal in bowl. When oil is hot enough, dip sliced cukes into egg mixture, then into flour mixture, forming a batter. Fry until light brown. Drain on cake rack covered with paper towels.

title: spaghetti and broccoli
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, saute garlic in 1/4 cup oil for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli; stir and cook for 5 minutes, until tender.
Cook spaghetti according to package; add hot spaghetti to broccoli, garlic and remaining oil.
Toss well.
Mix milk with cheese in separate bowl, then pour over spaghetti mixture over low heat.
Toss well until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix flour, soda, brown sugar, white sugar and salt.
Add vanilla, eggs and melted oleo.
Mix well and add chips.
Mix well. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour in mold and chill.

title: original chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla together. Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder, baking soda, chocolate chips, grated chocolate bar and chopped nuts together and add to creamed mixture.
Blend and chill.
Roll into size of golf balls. Put 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cherry dessert(fit for a king)
directions: Spread pie filling and pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish, sprinkle cake mix over fruit, place thin slices of butter over cake mix.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes (45 minutes is usually plenty) at 350°.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts over cake mix, if desired.
Serve warm or cold.

title: tomato soup dressing
directions: Put in glass jar and shake well before using.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Add beans, tomatoes and soup.
Pour mixture over Doritos in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Melt cheese on top.

title: famous fruit dip
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Serve with assorted fresh fruits such as strawberries, peaches, pears, pineapple or bananas.
Also, can serve with pound cake cubes.
Yields 2 cups.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse vegetables to separate.
Heat vegetables, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper to boil; stir frequently.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Follow directions on hand or electric freezer.
Let stand after it is churned and packed well for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Put in layers.
Dot each layer with half the butter.
Melt the rest of the butter with orange juice and brown sugar.
Blend well and pour over sweet potatoes.
Simmer, basting often, for about 15 minutes or bake at 400° for 15 minutes Sprinkle with cinnamon and/or nutmeg to taste (optional).

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese and mayonnaise; add onion and shrimp.
Serve on Ritz crackers or assorted crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Roll into small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or make refrigerator cookies by forming dough into 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Chill before baking or divide dough into 4 parts.
Make oblong rolls or put in deep freeze and bake next day or later. Dough will keep for a long period of time in deep freeze.
Bake next morning or any time about 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook oleo and onions until onion is tender.
Add broccoli, soup and water.
Cook about 10 minutes on low heat.
Add Cheez Whiz and rice.
Mix well.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken and chop in small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onions and peppers in butter or oleo and add Ro-Tel tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce; add cheese, peas and mushrooms.
Mix chicken and pasta.
Salt and pepper as desired. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Can be stored in freezer for a long period of time if tightly covered.

title: barbecued ham roast
directions: Place ham on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast at 325° until meat thermometer registers 130°, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: robby's banana hawaiian
directions: Brown coconut in skillet and set aside. Combine butter, sugar and cinnamon in skillet. Cook until sugar dissolves. Stir in rum and bring to a boil. Add bananas. Cook for 5 minutes on medium temperature. Spoon on top of ice cream. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: date carrot cake
directions: Drain pineapple well. Beat oleo and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Beat in pineapple, carrots, dates and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well blended. Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until cake tester comes clean. Cool completely. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 20.

title: hamburger-hash brown casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions
in
a
heavy skillet; drain.
Add potatoes, soup, sour cream and cheese and mix well.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch prepared
baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Top with canned onions and bake 15 minutes more.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add 1 at a time and beat well the 2 eggs.
Add bananas, nuts, flour, soda and salt.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pan needs to be well oiled.
Double the ingredients for 2 loaves.

title: crabmeat in a blanket
directions: Beat cream cheese, whipping cream and garlic at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in crabmeat and next 2 ingredients.
Trim crusts from bread slices.
Roll each slice to 1/8-inch thickness with a rolling pin.
Place 1 tablespoon crabmeat filling diagonally across each slice; fold opposite corners of bread to overlap in center.
Secure with wooden picks, if necessary.
Place sandwiches on ungreased baking sheets.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together and put half in pan (9 x 13-inch) or 2-quart mold.
Let set, then spread 1 small package of sour cream over. Pour rest of jello mixture on top and set.

title: lemonade pound cake
directions: Mix lemonade concentrate and sugar and let stand.
Put remaining ingredients into a large mixing bowl and beat until mixed well, about 3 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and immediately spoon lemonade mixture evenly over entire cake (in pan).
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Brown onions in drippings.
Take out and add meat.
After browning, add flour, salt, pepper, marjoram and thyme.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put ground beef into saucepan and cover with water. Cook until the ground beef is done; drain. Add all ingredients to ground beef; stir well and cook slow until thick.

title: rivel soup
directions: Slowly blend flour (with fork or pastry blender) into eggs. Add flour until mixture (pea size) crumbles.
Add crumbles slowly to boiling broth, stirring constantly, until all crumbles are added.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until tender, stirring often. Season to taste.

title: catfish nuggets
directions: Sprinkle the catfish with salt. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper lightly. Mix half and half yellow cornmeal and flour in gallon storage bag. Put in catfish pieces and shake to cover well. Use 6-quart cooker with it half full of peanut oil. Let get very hot. Slowly lower the heat. Fry the nuggets until golden brown.

title: pasties
directions: I use packaged pie crust.
Cut flank steak and pork into small pieces.
Grate potatoes, carrots and onion.
Put all in 1 large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll out dough larger than pie shape.
Place ingredients on dough (enough for 1/2 pie).
Place pat of butter on top and close up dough.
Put 3 slits in top of dough.
Bake at 425° for 55 minutes.
At the end of this time, put 1 tablespoon of water in the slits in each pie.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: corn pie, oyster pie, hot dog pie
directions: Cover with milk.
Cover with pie crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nut roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until light yellow.
Add oleo and beat. Dissolve yeast in a little warm water.
Add and beat again.
Add sour cream.
Sift together salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion.
Put salt over them and soak for 2 hours.
Drain cucumbers and onion after soaking.
Mix all other ingredients and heat and pour over cucumbers and onion.
Freeze.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut.
Spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Spread cake mix on top of the pecans and coconut.
Melt butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Pour on top of cake batter.
Bake according to directions on box of cake mix.

title: oreo cheese cake
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with margarine.
Press in bottom of large spring-form pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, eggs and egg yolks until smooth.
Pour over crust. (If desired, you can layer with cookies, filling, cookies and filling for layered effect.) Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 225° and bake 50 minutes. Test with toothpick (done when toothpick comes out clean).

title: chocolate amaretto cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with cocoa.
Place all ingredients, except chips, in a large bowl and beat 3 minutes.
Add chips; mix by hand.
Pour in pan and bake 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing to serving dish.
Use Amaretto Glaze for topping.

title: round steak and rice
directions: Brown steak and onions.
Arrange in layers in 2-quart casserole the meat, onions, rice, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Season each layer.
Rinse skillet with 1 cup water.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: johnny's favorite blueberry bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Stir in bananas.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spoon butter into a 7 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook until it springs back when touched in center.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt sweet and bitter chocolate in double boiler over hot water (remove from fire). Pour half in wax paper lined 9-inch square dish.
Pour marshmallows, morsels and nuts over chocolate. Pour remaining melted chocolate over all.
Spread gently to cover marshmallows.
When set, cut with warm knife. Refrigerate.
Remove pieces when cold. Wrap individually in plastic wrap.

title: marie's crab dip
directions: Combine crab, onions, parsley and lemon juice with enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Let stand several hours in refrigerator before serving.
Dip is very good served on your favorite snack crackers.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Soften peanut butter and margarine at room temperature.
Mix with powdered sugar.
Knead into balls, making them the size of a walnut.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and paraffin. Put balls on toothpicks and dip into chocolate, covering completely.
Place on waxed paper until chocolate sets up.
Store in covered container.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Make in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated italian garlic chicken
directions: Mix dressings and seasonings together.
Add chicken breasts. Cover; refrigerate 20 minutes (longer is okay).
Place on grill or broiler pan for 10 to 12 minutes on each side.

title: jogger's juice
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: fig cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add oil and eggs and beat well. Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix well. Stir in figs and pecans. batter will be a little thin.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Let cream cheese get soft.
Bake cake according to package directions.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch long baking pan.
Punch holes in the top of cake.
Pour pineapple over top of cake while hot.
Let cake get cold.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding; beat well.
Add water and cooking oil; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time-beat well after each.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients dry, then cut in shortening then sour milk.
Knead well and shape into a circle and cut cross in top.

title: baked onion dip
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, onion, parmesan cheese and garlic salt; stir in swiss chess.
Spoon into a 1-qt baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with the milk with a spoon or wire whisk. Blend in the Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with graham crackers, bottoms and sides.
Put half of the filling on top of the crackers, another layer of crackers, remaining pudding and layer of crackers.
Spread fudge chocolate icing on top and refrigerate.
Take from refrigerator 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice, curry powder and salt. Toss broccoli and chicken together with ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole pork chops
directions: In electric skillet, brown pork chops on both sides on medium heat.
Place 1 slice onion and 1 slice pepper on each pork chop (more if desired).
Blend tomato soup and 1/2 can water and pour over pork chops.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour. (May add a little more water while simmering.)
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and 1 egg.
Then add 2 more eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1/2 hour.

title: homemade swim ear solution
directions: Drop drops in each ear.

title: lemon salad dessert
directions: Mix.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan or large glass dish.
Use fingers to pat down.
Bake 20 minutes and cool.
(Can be done in microwave, about 10 minutes.)

title: grandmother wiley's jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Bake at 350°.
Use either caramel or white icing.
Cake is better if made days before serving.

title: best chocolate brownies
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and unsweetened chocolate squares over low heat.
Transfer chocolate mixture to a large mixer bowl.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until blended.
In a mixing bowl, stir together flour and baking powder.
Add to chocolate mixture along with the vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with the chopped walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and fill pie.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then turn down oven to 350° and bake for 40 minutes or until brown.
(This is a 2 crust pie.)

title: deer jerky
directions: Combine all the ingredients and let soak overnight.
Cook in a dehydrator for 10 to 12 hours, or a convection (air) machine for 2 to 3 hours at 200°.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cook cake mix by directions on box in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Let cake cool slightly.
Using a fork, poke holes in cake all the way to bottom of pan.
Make holes over the whole cake.
Mix milk and caramel topping together.
Pour over cake and let soak thoroughly Let cake cool and frost with whipped topping.
Crumble Butterfinger while still in wrapper.
Sprinkle over top of frosted cake.

title: simmered chinese chicken
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and brown chicken on all sides.
Mix together soy sauce, brown sugar, water, catsup, sherry, Tabasco sauce, garlic and green onion.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover, simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter.
Thicken pan juices with the cornstarch mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Spoon some sauce over chicken, sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve chicken with remaining sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and cook all together for 20 minutes or until thick.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, marshmallows and nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Sprinkle package of pudding mix over mixture and very rapidly mix together.
Place into container and refrigerate.

title: mary's miracle
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain excess fat.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, cream cheese, milk and egg. Cook, stirring until smooth and thick. Add broccoli.
Unroll 1 package crescent rolls on floured surface.
Place pieces together and seal seams.
Roll to fit a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.

Or use two triangles together, making 1 square piece and have individual sandwiches. Spread mixture over crust. Top with sliced Monterey Jack cheese and roll second package of crescent rolls to fit. Or, if making individual sandwiches, roll up the square making 1 bundle.
Seal edges, cut vents and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: my black bottom pie(yields one 9-inch pie; 6 generous servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Roll gingersnaps into fine crumbs; mix well with softened butter.
Line an ungreased 9-inch pie pan with the mixture, pressing crumbs against the bottom and sides.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Stir in flour and cook a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chili powder.
Then add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: yummy carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whisk eggs in large mixing bowl. Add oil, honey and yogurt; mix well. Add flour and stir thoroughly. Add baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Add grated carrot; mix well.
Scrape batter into a bread, cake or Bundt pan. Bake about 45 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cukes and onions.
Salt and let set overnight.
Heat, but do not boil, until clear.
Seal in jars.

title: plain cake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°.
Will make three layers.

title: copper pennies(carrot salad)
directions: Scrape carrots and boil in salted water until just tender (don't overcook).
Cool and slice.
Alternate carrots, pepper rings and onion rings in layers in a dish.
Beat remaining ingredients well until completely blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
This is better after being refrigerated for several hours.

title: grandma's manhattan clam chowder
directions: Saute chopped bacon and onion together over slow fire in stock-pot until bacon is crisp and onion is transparent.
Add cup of hot water and let stand.
Boil potatoes and carrots in remaining hot water.
When partially done, add bacon mixture.
Add tomatoes and clams, with liquid, to pot; break bay leaves and add with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, an hour or more, adding water if needed.
Makes about six servings.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, vanilla, milk, water and egg yolks.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
When thickened, pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites for meringue. Brown meringue in a hot oven.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Grease well 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cranberries on bottom of pie pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs well; add 1 cup sugar gradually and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add flour, butter, vanilla and melted shortening to egg/sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Pour batter over cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.
Cut like pie.
Serve either warm or cold with scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: company casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a large casserole. Put 6 pieces of chicken on top and then add onion soup mixture over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
You can shorten time by baking in microwave for 10 to 15 minutes first.

title: open crabmeat sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients and mix together, except muffins.
Spread on muffins.
Broil until spread bubbles.
Serves 4.

title: italian pot roast
directions: In large skillet, saute onions, celery, green peppers, and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasoning. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Brown meat in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add mixture to meat.
Simmer in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Turn meat often.
Cook spaghetti and place around roast. Serve with sauce from meat pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients, plus 3/4 cup of water, in a blender; mix well.

title: english pea salad
directions: Boil vinegar, oil, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Let cool. Drain all vegetables.
Combine.
Pour boiled mixture over vegetables.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll out; cut shapes with cookie cutter.
Decorate.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 1/2 to 1 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend 1/3 sugar with peanut butter.
Alternately add remaining sugar and milk. Add vanilla. Makes enough for two 9-inch round layers.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in beaten whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: orange surprise balls
directions: Mix 1/2 box sugar and all other ingredients together.
Shape into balls and roll in remaining half of powdered sugar.
Makes 50 balls.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a 1	1/2
quart
dish,
stir together sugar and corn syrup. Cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes and stir.	Add vanilla and butter;
microwave	1
to
minutes
on High.
Add soda; stir quickly until light and foamy.
Pour into buttered baking sheet and cool.
Break into serving pieces.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small saucepan; boil and cook 10 minutes.
Drain and squeeze excess liquid.
Combine spinach mixture and remaining ingredients.
Stir, then cover and chill for 2 hours. Shape mixture into balls.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Chill for 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add nuts or coconut, as desired. Pour into Jell-O mold or oblong dish.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a small bowl, stir together 2 tablespoons flour and sugar. Set aside.

In heavy saucepan over medium heat, bring cranberry sauce to a boil, stirring often. Stir in flour and sugar mixture. Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring frequently, 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and orange peel.
Place in freezer to cool slightly.
In a large bowl, stir together 1 1/2 cups flour, oats, brown sugar, walnuts, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Using wooden spoon, stir in butter until mixture is well combined and crumbly.
Using fingers, press half of dough firmly and evenly over bottom of prepared pan. Spread cranberry mixture evenly over dough.
Sprinkle remaining dough evenly over filling. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until light brown. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
With sharp knife, cut into 24 bars. Store in airtight container.

title: fruit punch bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and cocktail with syrup.
Spread in greased cookie sheet pan. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, drizzle with glaze and cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crock-pot cheese dip
directions: Combine in crock-pot and melt.
Serve hot with tortilla chips, party crackers, bread and/or mixed raw vegetables.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine milk and cold water and heat.
Pour hot liquid over butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm. Stir in 2 cups flour, dissolved yeast and oats.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead about 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic. Shape to form ball.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat surface of dough. Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 hour until doubled in size.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of baking pan.
Add chicken, then pour premixed soups and water over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Leave uncovered 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with aluminum foil for last hour.

title: jello salad dessert
directions: Mix; chill until thickened (not set).
Spoon on cheese layer and chill.

title: play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat until all the mixture sticks together.
Roll into a ball and let cool.
Keep in plastic bags when not in use.

title: raspberry custard brulee(low calorie)
directions: Gently rinse berries, drain.
Divide berries evenly among 4 (6-ounce) ovenproof custard cups, set aside.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in small saucepan, stir well.
Add egg, stir well. Gradually add milk, stirring well.
Cook over low heat 12 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, let cool 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and vanilla; stir well.
Spoon custard mixture evenly over raspberries.
Place custard cups on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Boil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 2 minutes or until sugar melts.
Serve warm.
Approximately 122 calories per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook boxes of Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake, covered, with foil for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and milk and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla.
Quickly add oats and stir until mixed well.
Quickly drop by teaspoon on wax paper and allow to cool.
Work quickly or ingredients will harden in the pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt, crushed red pepper and chopped onions. Then add egg and milk and stir just enough to thoroughly moisten dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoon into hot deep fat (360°) and fry 2 to 4 minutes until golden brown. Drain on a paper towel. Yields 2 dozen.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Stir
all ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Bake on sprayed cookie sheet at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May use to make patties
or loaf.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green onions, bell pepper and peas.

Sprinkle bacon bits on top of these ingredients. Mix sugar with mayonnaise and spread on top of bacon bits. Sprinkle cheese over bacon bits. Better if made the night before and mayonnaise is allowed to seep through lettuce mixture.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for one hour and fifteen minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and cottage cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Mix well and pour over broccoli.
Melt butter; add bread crumbs.
Stir to coat. Pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple.
Add a few drops of cherry juice to sweeten dip.
Serve with potato chips or snack crackers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Add 2 cans of shrimp.
Whip until shrimp are broken up.
Chill.
When ready to serve, sprinkle top with paprika for a dash of color.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Layer in casserole dish small amount of bread crumbs, chicken, cream of chicken soup, bread crumbs, chicken, cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1 cup chicken broth and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter; add onions and cook until tender.
Add meat, cook until done.
Stir in flour; add mushrooms and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup, cook for 10 minutes on low.
Add buttermilk and cook until hot.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Whip ingredients together.
Add vegetable oil, eggs, milk and almond, then fold in poppy seed.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: blueberry & black cherry jello salad
directions: Bring cup of juice to a boil and add to jello. Then add cold water, blueberries, and pineapple. Congeal. Top with following topping.

title: vegetarian cabbage
directions: Pour in 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan (well-greased and floured). Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli side dish
directions: Cook broccoli.
Add salt.
Cook until tender.
Pour in baking dish.
Add 1 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Roll Ritz crackers into crumbs.
Put on top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Cream oil and sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in egg whites and oats mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 14 large muffins.

title: raw pear cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon, then
nuts and raisins with a little flour mixed with them.
Bake at 300° in tube pan for 1 hour or until done (grease and flour pan).

title: cabbage
directions: Put salt, pepper and oil in boiling water.
Add cabbage.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: cockeyed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make three holes in dry ingredients.
Put oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in the other.
Pour 1 cup water and stir until flour is wet and all is combined.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost if desired. Makes a very moist devil's food cake.

title: artichoke-thistle dip
directions: Place artichoke hearts in food processor.
Coarsely chop.
Add remaining ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Transfer to bowl and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with assorted crudites.

title: easy beef in wine
directions: Place
all
ingredients
in
a	2
1/2 quart casserole. Cover tightly
(use lid or foil) and cook at 300° for 3 hours. Don't peek.
Let the steam do the cooking!
Serve over rice or noodles!

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and add 7-Up pop.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef with horseradish sauce
directions: Brown meat in 4 teaspoons butter and remove to casserole. Brown onion in 2 teaspoons butter.
Add to casserole with curry powder, ginger, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and wine.
Bake covered in slow oven at 300°
about 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: "lite" lime salad
directions: Drain pears.
Save juice in saucepan.
Bring juice to boil, when it starts to boil, dissolve jello in juice.
Let it cool. Cream cheese and pears in mixer.
Then mix in cooled lime jello, Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: david's ham rolls
directions: You will need 1 toothpick.

title: lemon cream tarts(low fat)
directions: Pre-heat oven to 325°.
Combine eggs, milk, 1 Tbsp. grated lemon rind, and lemon juice in a bowl; whisk until blended and pour into crust.
Bake for 30 minutes or until filling is set; cool.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with strips of lemon rind. Makes 10 servings.

title: mixed vegetables and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain fat.
Cook vegetables in pan until most of liquid is gone.
Add beef and tomato soup to vegetables.
Mix well.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Empty milk in saucepan and melt in marshmallows over low heat while stirring.
Put cracker crumbs in a pan and pour this over it.
Add all other ingredients and mix to a thick dough.
Press in whatever you want and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Dump out and you have a fruit cake that is delicious.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Boil water and add margarine.
Let margarine melt.
Add flour, all at once.
Stir quickly until it forms into a ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool for about 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread on lightly greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
After removing from oven, flatten any bubbles that have formed.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Add these ingredients to the rest of crumb mixture.
Mix and put in 2 large greased pie pans.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts to reserved crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of dough.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy sugared walnuts
directions: Put all in big pot; bring to boil.
Mix with large spoon until pot is more or less dry.
Put on buttered large cookie sheet; put in preheated oven at 300° for 20 minutes, then let cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients together until candy forms a soft ball (238°), then add the marshmallow cream and peanut butter. Beat until smooth and mixture loses gloss. Pour into buttered pan or dish.

title: poppy seed cake(the best)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, stirring to blend.
Beat at medium speed 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn onto cake plate.
Sift confectioners sugar on top.

title: edible peanut butter dough
directions: Mix all together to make dough.
Makes 1 serving.

title: better than pastor's sermons cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.

title: tassies
directions: Boil
margarine,
butter
and sugar together for 2 minutes. Put a single layer of graham crackers in shallow baking pan. Pour
butter
mixture
over
crackers.
Sprinkle
with chopped pecans.
Bake
10 minutes at 350°.	Remove from pan as soon as done.
Place
on foil or wax paper.
Break apart when cool. Great!!

title: vegetable spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with crackers, rye bread, fresh vegetable dippers or serve in a hollowed out bread bowl or bell pepper.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine fruits, raisins and wine.
Cover and let stand overnight.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, eggs, cinnamon, cloves, baking soda and salt.
Beat until well mixed, scraping the sides of bowl.
Stir in fruit mixture and nuts.
Spread batter evenly in greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.
Yields about 4 dozen bars.
May be cooked in greased miniature tins, fill about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Yields about 40 round cakes.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Make a ring mold by cutting off top and bottom of tuna can. Place mold on plate.
Put 4 shrimp on bottom.
Toss avocado with lime juice and cilantro.
Put 1/4 of avocado on top of shrimp and press down.
Add layer of halved cherry tomatoes.
Make tomato vinaigrette by combining chopped tomato, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/4 vinaigrette around outside of ring.
Remove ring.
Top with chives.
Repeat on 3 other plates.
Serves 4 as appetizer or first course salad.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°; grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine mashed potatoes, cream cheese, onion, eggs, flour, salt and pepper in a mixer.
Beat for 2 or 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour into prepared casserole dish; spread French fried onions over top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: mother's cranberry ice
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 1/4 cups water until skins burst.
Mash through sieve and cool.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water and pinch of salt.
Boil for 10 minutes until syrupy.
Cool.
Add salt to egg white and beat until stiff.
Add syrup to cranberry pulp, then add the beaten white of egg.
Turn into a freezing tray and freeze.
After mixture freezes to a "mushy" consistency, stir in tray with a fork.
If served as a dessert, use 1 1/4 cups sugar.

title: chili
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients in large saucepan.
Brown meat; drain.
Add the next 10 ingredients; stir to blend.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: peach cake
directions: Combine and sprinkle on top of cake batter before baking. Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: susan's party meatballs
directions: Mix in a bowl hamburger, chopped onion, eggs, saltine crackers (crushed fine) and garlic powder.
Mix well; drop by balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown. Place on paper towel to absorb grease.
In a pot, mix chili sauce and grape jelly on low heat.
Heat until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs, serve hot with toothpicks.

title: cherry winks(yields about 5 dozen)
directions: Measure corn flakes; crush into coarse crumbs.
Set aside. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Measure margarine and sugar into a large mixing bowl; beat until very light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix until combined.
Stir in nuts, dates and finely cut cherries.
Shape level measuring tablespoons of dough into balls.
Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheets; top each cookie with a cherry quarter.
Bake in oven at 375° for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheets; cool on wire racks.

title: creamy nachos
directions: Brown meat and onions.	Drain.	Add salt and pepper.
Stir in Rotel, chili and beans.
Heat.
Dice cheese in mixture and melt. Stir in sour cream.
Serve hot with white chips.
Serves 6-8.

title: italian vegetable dish
directions: Place eggplant, tomato, zucchini, onion and garlic in microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces; fry in large kettle until almost crisp.
Chop peeled onions very fine; toss in and cook until limp. Add finely diced carrots, celery and chopped parsley.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Drain tomatoes; put liquid in measuring cup.
Toss tomatoes in with vegetable mixture.
Drain clams and add clam juice to tomato liquid.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 pints of juice.
Pour into kettle and season with salt, peppercorns, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and cook gently 45 minutes.
Toss in fine potatoes; cover and cook 20 minutes longer.
Add chopped clams; cook slowly, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together sour cream, whipped topping, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in fruits and nuts. Turn into a slightly greased 4 1/2 cup ring mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve frozen!

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease three 9-inch layer cake pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper.
Stir flour with sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in walnuts, coconut, carrots and pineapple.
Divide batter evenly in prepared pans.
Bake in middle of oven for 30 to 35 minutes until a pick comes out clean.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and dice boiled potatoes.
Place in casserole dish and salt sparingly.
Combine soup, milk and Cheez Whiz in a saucepan and heat until blended.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: non cholesterol applesauce cake
directions: Use Fleischmann's margarine.
It is no cholesterol.

title: scallops and pasta
directions: Saute garlic in butter and oil. Add mushrooms, parsley, wine and lemon juice.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add scallops. Cook until done, 2 to 4 minutes. Add wine.
Serve over angel hair.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine together. Add salt, pepper and flour. Stir in Rice Krispies. Shape into balls and press with a fork. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Brown meat. Place layers of potatoes, onions, celery and beans in a large buttered casserole. Add meat and seasonings. Pour tomato soup over all. Cover and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Carrots are also good in this.

title: german chocolate love bites
directions: Mix dry cake mix, dry pudding mix, oil, egg, vanilla and flour with mixer on low speed.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.
While cookies are baking, unwrap foil from candy Kisses.
After taking cookies from oven, let them cool on baking sheet for a minute or two.
Then firmly press a candy Kiss on top.
Cool completely before removing from cookie sheets.
Makes approximately 36 cookies.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce mix, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat. Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, Ricotta cheese, spinach and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Alternate layers of lasagna noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken meal
directions: Layer in casserole dish the cooked noodles, rice, chicken, vegetables and soup mixture.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into slices 3/4-inch thick.
Dip into egg, then into bread crumbs.
Carefully dip into egg and crumbs again. Melt butter in large skillet on low heat.
Add green tomato slices and cook slowly until golden on each side (turning only once).
Tomatoes will be tender.
Season to taste at table.
Serve hot. Yields 4 servings.

title: tasty tomato salad
directions: Core and slice tomatoes thinly from the top to the bottom, not from side to side.
When coring, remove only that part where the stem has fastened to the tomato. Slice as thin as possible.
Layer in flat bottom bowl.

title: mons german chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut and nuts.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened (about 12 to 15 minutes).
Add coconut and nuts.
Cool until thick and spread on cake.

title: garden frittata
directions: Place broccoli and carrots in a steamer basket.
Place basket over boiling water.
Cover; steam for 8 to 10 minutes or just until tender.
In a medium bowl beat eggs with the cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in steamed vegetables and mushrooms.
In a 10-inch skillet or omelet pan, melt butter.
Pour in egg mixture and cook over medium heat, lifting edges occasionally to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath, until top is almost set and bottom is lightly browned.
Place skillet under broiler 5 inches from heat, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Top with tomato slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; broil about 1 minute longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into well greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. For a more moist cake, do not drain strawberries and bake about 15 minutes longer.

title: century manor rice
directions: Brown Rosa Marina in butter or oil.
Add rice and stir; pour in water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let set 20 to 30 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
Will serve many.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put vegetables through a food chopper and sprinkle with salt. Marinate
overnight
in
covered
bowl in refrigerator, then drain and
rinse with cold water.
Mix and heat together remaining ingredients.
Mix
with
squash
and
boil	20 to 30 minutes. Pack in hot jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Crush candy bars and fold into cool whip.
Put into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let cheese and margarine become soft.
Work all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: omi's egg drop
directions: Simmer beef bones through Maggi in 2 1/2 quarts water for 2 hours.
Strain; add bouillon cubes to broth.
Take eggs through milk, put in blender and whip.
Put in double boiler until set. Cut into squares.
Put squares in bowls.
Pour broth over it.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a skillet heat bacon drippings or oil on medium-high heat. Add rice; cook and stir until rice is golden brown.
Add onion and garlic; stir and cook 3 additional minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, on medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring only once after 10 minutes.
Check rice for doneness by tasting a few top grains.
If rice is firm, add a little hot water and cook about 3 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: father clark's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, peanut butter and milk until smooth; mix well and then add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Fold in the Cool Whip and pour into the graham cracker crust.
Place in freezer for 2 hours.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in oil in skillet until it starts to wilt.
Add water; cover and simmer on low 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in soup. Warm through.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Can be put under broiler to toast crumbs.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Combine the first five (5) ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth with electric mixer.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.
Form into large ball.
Roll in pecans or walnuts.
Wrap in wax paper or Handi-Wrap.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place corn and nuts in brown grocery bag.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, and salt in a 2-quart bowl. Microwave mixture on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until mixture comes to a boil.
Microwave 2 more minutes. Stir in baking soda until fluffy.
Pour over corn.
Shake well. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Microwave 1/2 minute again, then shake.
Pour onto cookie sheet or wax paper to cool.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place roast in electric skillet with 1/4 cup water.
Cook at low temperature for 3 to 4 hours or until very tender.
Shred with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until onions are very tender.
Serve on rolls.
Yields 12 servings.

title: lucy's baked tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with bits of butter.
Bake at 350°.

title: diabetic cake (white)
directions: Bake at 350°.
Combine vegetable oil, Sweet 'N Low, vanilla and egg; cream together.
Add flour and milk; mix well.
Grease pan; bake until golden brown and toothpick comes out dry.
May add fresh fruit for different cakes.

title: suicide bars
directions: Melt milk, chocolate chips and 3 tablespoons butter in double boiler over low heat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and chopped nuts.
In mixing bowl, cream together the margarine, brown sugar and eggs. Mix flour, soda, salt, oats, nuts and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Press 2/3 oat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over oat mixture. Crumble remaining oat mixture over chocolate. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sinfully delicious!

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in milk.
Mix all ingredients together to form dough.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: parmesan asparagus
directions: Bring big pot of water to boil.
Add asparagus and cook about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Brush ovenproof dish with butter and arrange asparagus in it.
Pour rest of butter over the top and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Turn spears so that they are well coated.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese, grind a little pepper and dash on a little salt.
Bake asparagus in preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Jell-O together, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Beat in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Grease heated griddle.
Pour about 3 tablespoons batter from tip of large spoon.
Cook until puffed and edges are dry. Turn and cook until other side is golden brown.

title: nanny's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on until fork can go through easily. Boil eggs until they are hard-boiled.
Cut potatoes into small pieces and place in large bowl.
Dice eggs, celery and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cook broccoli as package directs, but only cook for 10 minutes.
Cook rice as package directs, adding bouillon cube to the water.
When cooked, toss rice with parsley and spread over bottom of greased casserole dish; arrange chicken on top of rice.
Mix lite cream with broccoli and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle over all with grated cheese and bake 25 minutes in preheated 400° oven or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is lightly browned.
Sometimes I use regular broccoli and a can of Cheddar cheese soup.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: muttie's lemon bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with one layer of graham crackers.
Mix butter, sugar, milk and egg in saucepan.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add walnuts, coconut and crushed graham crackers.
Pour over single layer of graham crackers.
Cover mixture with another layer of graham crackers.
Make frosting by mixing 1/2 cup butter, confectioners sugar, vanilla and the juice of lemon until smooth. Frost top layer of graham crackers.
Chill 6 hours or overnight. Cut into 6 bars.

title: strawberry kool-aid
directions: Pour Kool-Aid in 1 large pitcher.
Put sugar in pitcher and water.
Stir.
Add ice and strawberries and enjoy.

title: watergate
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Then pour into a pan and refrigerate and decorate with slices of kiwi or peach.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cut ham into small squares.
Finely chop onion.
Mix all ingredients except small serving of ham.
Roll into log.
Sprinkle remaining ham around the log.

title: old fashion grape pie
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or two knives.
Do not overmix.
Add water gradually, sprinkling 1 tablespoon at a time.
Should not feel wet.
Use only enough water to hold the pastry together when pressed.
Roll dough into a round ball.
Divide into two portions and roll out on a lightly floured board.
Fit one shell into pie dish.
Remaining dough is for top crust.

title: 4 spice casserole
directions: Cut American cheese slices into 1/2-inch strips.
Saute onion and stir in seasonings, tomatoes and soup.
Add rice.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add can of diced chik, partially drained.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and top with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted. Garnish with sliced stuffed olives.
Serves 4.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight or 4 to 5 hours. Cook with all ingredients until tender. Add water in pot to about 4-inches from top. (Needs room to simmer or will boil over.) Usually takes about 3 hours (to be well done).

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Blend dry ingredients and place with apples in crust.
Add apple juice.
Add crust and seal edges.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until crust is brown or apples tender.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices.
Beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin, cream and milk, mixing well after each addition.
Pour in crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 375° and bake 30 minutes more until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and place in a large casserole or deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rich pecan pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Butter inside and around edge of each unbaked pie shell.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: breakfast scones
directions: Combine
egg
and
milk.
Mix with Bisquick.
Add sugar, rind and
raisins.
Stir with fork until soft dough is formed. Knead for
30 seconds on floured board.
Divide dough into two equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a circle a half inch thick. Cut each
circle
into
6 triangles.
Place on buttered cookie sheet. Brush
tops with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Bring to a rolling boil oleo, butter and brown sugar.
Add broken nuts.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Place crackers on a cookie sheet.
Pour hot mixture over them.
Cool and cut or you can bake at 300° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: jac's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spam casserole
directions: Brown onion and Spam in butter or oleo until onions are cooked.
Add mushroom soup, milk, ketchup and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in rotini.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: corn beef casserole
directions: Mix in 3-quart bowl.
Put all in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup broken potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mexican sweet potatoes
directions: Beat all together.
